review: i chose fluenz over rosetta stone after reading lots of reviews  i know that my own learning style is one where i need to understand the grammar why things are the way they are etc  it sounds like rosetta stone is much more learning by absorbingrote memorization whereas fluenz promised to teach you why x goes before y etc  overall fluenz has delivered on its promises and im very happy with the way im learning italian and the style of teachingin short fluenz combines an onscreen teacher who really humanizes the language and explains things very well with reading writing listening speaking and various matching games to get you to internalize all those different aspects of the language its well thought out and quite logically done  i would really recommend this to anyone who wants to get to grips with the way a language is put together and to build a solid foundation from which you can really understand italian  im only half way through but feel really great about what ive learned so farmy complaints are minor but i think worth noting repetitivenesspredictability  each individual lesson becomes a little bit repetitive in the sense that youre sayingtypinglistening to the same  or  sentences over and over again in each lesson  i see why theyre doing this but the problem is it gets to the point where you know whats coming before it actually comes on screen  all the sentences appear in the same order in each sentence so youre not thinkinglistening as much as remembering part of learning is being given variations you have to figure out for yourselves based on what you already know  this is kinda doing the opposite theres also not that much variation between lessons  i realize this is hard in a computer format but some games or some sort of variety would be appreciated matching pictures with words  this is really silly sometimes  they give you one word and four pictures and ask you to match the word to the correct picture  a good exercise  but sometimes the word actually appears in the picture though  for example how about finding a picture of a menu that doesnt contain the word menu in it there are quite a few of these where the thinking is done for youthe answer is given away sonias outfit  she always wears the same thing  does she not have a change of clothes   except for those very minor complaints this software is awesome very well thought out and very enjoyable to learn italian from
product: learn italian fluenz italian  for mac pc iphone ipad amp android phones version

review: this program is exactly what the title says it is it gives a pretty good introduction to guitar playing most of the songs have an option to view a picture of the top of the fret board while someone else is playing the song what i dont like about this feature is that the fingers show up as simple dots and dont really show how a persons hand is supposed to move for the chord changes this program also gives the option to watch someone else play the song which sounds like a great idea but it really doesnt add much my biggest problem with guitars is that i cannot figure out what i am doing wrong in some sections i was really hopping that the feature where you get to watch someone else play would help me figure it out what i really learned is that wrong or right people look the same playing the guitar this program does not help you figure out problems if you started from a cold start not knowing anything as the title says for dummies then this might have worked better for me but im not sure i wouldnt have run into the same problems previous programs by emedia have allowed for the option of plugging in a midi device that allows the program to test and tell you based on what you are playing if you are doing something right i was really looking forward to being able to use that on this program however there is no such thing on this program i felt that was a draw back to other emedia programs and this product is made by emedia and for dummies so i felt that was disapointing the other problem with the program is that once you get past several lessons they get into real songs and instead of focusing on the guitar playing they have someone singing and its very distracting as a musician of many instruments brassstrings any musician practices again and again the parts they are having difficulty with and the goal is to play your part correctly the singing on a guitar playing tutorial program was very distracting the good parts of this program are that it does explain concepts very well the idea of the slash chord vs power chords are explained well and the exercises reflect the lessons they are teaching in each chapter i feel that this is a great alternative to taking a class filled with other people however im not convinced that its much more effective than a book and a music cd could have been  this program is focused on rockblues and does not touch at all on standard music notation or classical guitar in anyway once a lesson is done there are review screens that go back and quiz you or become reference screens for chords it is very easy to see this book as a sequence and really see how to have a great foundation for guitar playing
product: emedia guitar for dummies

review: since this is a upgrade version let me talk for experienced flash users  macromedia seems to have taken a few right steps in integrating flash mx with its other products like dreamweaver ultradev and cold fusion server mx acquired from allaire even though cold fusion mx is at a beta  stage right now its easy to see some of the powerful multimedia features being integrated into the macromedia products based on thatsome of the best new changes in flash mx that warrant an upgrade are actionscript the scripting language that powers flash interactivity is now easier to write and analyze flash mx has a fully functional script editor with features similar to those found in its other programs like dreamweaver cold fusion studio and homesite the editor helps both experienced and beginning programmers write valid actionscript by providing codehinting autoformatting and searchandreplace functions flash mx also contains a complete debugger for the first time flash is offering a collection of templates to simplify the production of standard web documents such as ads slide shows and tutorials in addition the templates are smart for example a photo album template includes all the programming necessary for a photo slideshow a lot of ui components like scroll bars check boxes and list boxes that previously had to be laboriously created are now included in flash mx the appropriate behaviors are built into these objects so adding functional interface elements to an application is a simple draganddrop operation one of the biggest changes in flash mx is the integration of video the integrated video support provided by the sorenson spark codec can import standard video formats such as avi mpeg or quicktime and convert them to a streaming format that is displayed natively by the flash mx player the import filter can also resize the video or sync the frame rate to the flash movie when converting a file flash mx also provides a powerful tool to modify vector shapes flashs free transform tool is similar to the free transform tools found in standard illustration programs like freehand and illustrator the program lets you rotate size skew and distort objects a special bounding boxcalled an envelopelets you manipulate an objects shape using control points and tangent handles this kind of makes me wonder what itll do to the already overpriced macromedia freehand software a lot of changes have been made to animation processes to make it more efficient the import filter for fireworks png files now intelligently preserves text and vector shapes which will make life a lot easier headline animations are easier to update because flash now maintains individual characters as editable text rather than as nontext vector shapes some changes have changed the visual appearance of flash mx workspace now you can dock and collapse palettes and you have the ability to define and switch between different palette configurations like developer designer etc to optimize the workspace for design or coding layers can be organized into folders the new properties inspector offers an easy way to change an objects basic attributes quickly the library function has also been improved by allowing sharing of symbols between documents flash automatically tracks the original location of each symbol and autoupdates all instances in all documents if the original is modifiedas i mentioned macromedia seems to be moving towards integrating their other products as a result some powerful new features in flash mx await the development of other products in the mx line macromedia has already announced flash server solutions which will consist of a gateway and a communications server the latter will allow developers to add realtime messaging as well as twoway audio and video to flash applicationsi think upgrading to the new version is not even a question
product: flash mx upgrade

review: i read the reviews and decided to take a chance with this item  the problems i did see i figured i could work through  so here is my updated story about how things went once i received the item and gave it a shotmy pc is middle of the road  i have windows  home premium  bit a  ghz intel dual core cpu  gb of ram and  gb of video ram with directx  and it seems i was teetering on the edge with being able to use the roxio software  i give it a  out of  just because the usb card does its job well  so here is my story and some advice for someone in my shoes with a similar pc who is considering giving it a shotthe installation was a bear  it took longer than other roxio products ive used  after the installation i then updated the usb drivers available on the roxio website  the program itself is fairly straightforward to use but it is not what they talk it up to be  the editing tools are inadequate you get more from windows live movie maker  also no matter what i do to my computer the program still lags horribly at the one hour mark when recording  the lag lasts for two or three minutes and it recovers  but chunks of the recording are then missing and i have to go back and rerecord the missing sections then edit them in  however ive ditched the roxio recording software for something much more dependable windows movie maker  to avoid all these issues  it is easy to use requires fewer system resources works on windows  and much more stable  a  minute recording only takes  gb of space on movie maker  where it takes  gb on the roxio software and the quality is virtually the same  this may help people with older machines  search for portable movie maker on cnets software downloading website and it should be third on the list  it is not a virus as people suggest in the reviews it scans clean with my antivirus software  i also noticed that the usb card gets hot enough to concern me  overheating can cause hardware failure so i now point a fan on it to cool it while recording and the quality of the recording seems a little better too  the roxio program does a poor job of converting  the av sync is terrible and gets worse the further into the movie it goes  do not use it for converting  it also takes double the time of other softwareso here is how to use this  install the program just to get the drivers for the usb card  do not use the roxio program  then update the drivers from the roxio website  download portable movie maker from cnet and use it to capture your video  when recording make sure to point a fan at your usb card to keep it cool  if you want to convert your video use another program to perform this task  i recommend bigasoft total video converter it is  and worth it  ive heard that there are free converters floating around that do a decent job as well so just do your research
product: roxio easy vhs to dvd old version

review: i waited a very long time to review this product because i wanted to get some use out of it before making a final call  if you have some familiarity with advanced photoillustration editing or video editing software youll have an advantage with this program as it utilizes some similar tools and functions making it easier to really use this  if the extent of your computer editing stops at paint youre going to be overwhelmed  this program is a big comfortable step below higher end professional animation programs but i wouldnt say its for an absolute beginneranime studio debut  features an introductory guide in a pdf format that walks a new user through a step by step process in creating a scene learning to animate and learning to create  its slow learning at first and then quickly you get the hang of the process  this introductory guide was one of the easiest ive had to follow and really simplified the program so that you could learn and become familiar with all the tools while creating something new  my only beef was that a few of the tutorial character files they mentioned were not located on my hard drive and i couldnt find the files anywhere  so i made due with other characters and still learned the processi remember years ago in college learning  modeling and animation on a very early version of lightwave  the goal of the entire semester was to design a realistic table and chair  which took a lot of patience and time to design  in a fraction of that time i created an entire animated scene including a table and chair in anime studio that ended up looking quite nice and with only the introductory pdf as a guide  while anime studio is nowhere near as complete intense or powerful as lightwave i think it offers a great affordable alternative for the casual creative who wants to animate and create  designspicking up the programs basics is easy once you get familiar with the tools but ive kind of plateaued a bit and find that i struggle trying to get my animation to do everything i imagine it doing however this is my failure not the programs  overall im actually much more pleased with this program than i expected to be  its more powerful than i expected and i would recommend this to friend who are looking for something similar
product: anime studio debut   old version

review: sadly windows  is probably more maligned than it ought to be in situations that call for more limited input and minimal multitasking like a tablet or htpc windows  actually works fairly well the issue comes when microsoft basically forced it onto the desktop workspace and the fact is that windows  just isnt a desktop os the start button is gone the desktop that were used to is neutered really what makes windows well windows the native windows  apps are fullscreen affairs and as far as the ui goes it just seems like a major step backward for those who actually work on a pc windows  basically makes you take a hop step and a jump where would cold just turn and step in windows  productivity takes a hit this is why the businesses arent adopting it and thats why windows  is failingit works well enough on tablets and htpcs imho but i had to dock it an extra star because ive had nothing but bad luck with it my htpc was running windows  pro so i opted to use the upgrade there i had to basically erase everything and start fresh with the upgrade but thats frankly how i prefer to do it anyways the upgrade process went smoothly and was less timeconsuming than i would have guessed all but one driver was installed and the os was running well i started to install my apps and standard desktop programs without a hitch so far so good the next day i fired it up to continue downloading some things and play a game on steam only to have the system bluescreen on me that isnt that big a deal in and of itself not my first rodeo with windows osesbluescreens are almost a certainty at some point but the options available to deal with it are vague at best guessing the refresh is akin to the repair install in windows xp while the full reset is a more traditional windows reinstall since it gets rid of whatever you have on the pc the fact that none of them worked is also disappointingso here i am with a nonfunctional pc that had been fine for a couple of years using windows  that in and of itself isnt a condemnation of the windows  os again kind of used to it by this point but the fact that the os itself is so not compelling that im strongly considering going back to  probably is as it now stands i cant really think of a single compelling reason to upgrade to windows  especially on a traditional desktop or nontouchenabled laptop windows  simply wasnt designed with those platforms the vast majority of the pc market mind you inmindupdate ultimately the issue that i was having was due to a bad hard drive so i cant fault windows  for that once i received the replacement from western digital i reinstalled windows  and this time all went well well thats not entirely correcteverything went well until activation it wouldnt workat all i searched and saw that this has been an ongoing issue since windows  was in public beta and it still has not been resolved luckily for me the overly tedious phone activation did work but that shouldnt be necessary and yes my wireless network adaptor and router are working properly it also wouldnt activate over a wired connectionthe pc worked well enough until this morning steam works diablo iii installed without a hitch all of my standard apps as far as compatibility goes its been great i turn on the pc today only to see that it needs to restart due to updates okthats typical microsoft there so i restart nothing the system posts windows  begins to boot and then goes to a black screenthats it apparently this is another ongoing issue and after pressing  to go into the repair process windows tells me that my system is unable to boot properly thanks for the tip it tells me that its going to do a restore and it does my system starts thats all fine and good but im growing a bit weary of hoopjumping its obvious to me that windows  isnt ready for primetime its got all of the typical bugs that typify a microsoft os once those are out of the way and once microsoft repairs the neutered desktop windows  might be something to consider but as things are youd do better to wait unless you really really like the modern metro ui andor halfbaked apps theres no real reason to upgrade to windows update im done microsoft the pc had been running normally until this morning upon booting i notice that i have no connectivity so i go to troubleshoot my wireless connection windows crasheshard the pc restarts and i can tell something is wrong because its taking forever long story short and three hours worth of repair attempts later and ive made my decision to go back to windows  the repairs dont work the new frowny bsods give precious little information no error codes just microsofts condolences and a vague error message telling me that my system configuration information was badyay i just want a computer that works and the only thing i use this pc for is gaming and the occasional movie have it in the living room so far windows  has been a nightmare maybe ill give it another chance once  hits but until then im reverting to windows  for my sanitys sake and that drops my rating to onesame as any other product that cant be used asadvertised
product: microsoft windows   upgrade old version

review: professor samuel hunt is a researcher at the british museum in   hes looking for something really special that will make his name in his field and one night he finds it in the form of an anonymous letter  the letter contains the page of an old book or codex and warns that unless professor hunt solves its mysteries certain doom will fall upon us all  of course the good professor sets out at once driven less by a sense of heroism than by intellectual curiosityagon  the mysterious codex comprises the first three episodes of a  game originally released for download only the remaining episodes will be available as they are produced first via download and then on cd or dvd  in it you will explore the british museum the icy wilds of lapland and the jungles of madagascar in search of the ancient game of nations the game is mainly first person with some third person cutscenes  there are no timed puzzles and you cant diei was immediately struck by the beauty of agon  the backgrounds are simply incredible as are the animations which often transform a watercolour stillshot into a moving scene  the character animations are a little sketchier but still quite good  while im on game basics most of those were above par as well  voice acting was very good  sounds were subtly integrated into the whole  music was little used but what there was was fine  some written materialletters and journalswere very lovely with intensely picturesque writing although the handwriting fonts used were sometimes hard to decipher and a little fadedthe puzzles in agon are a wide assortment dominated by inventory and decoding messages  one long message in morse code takes patience and a plan  in another place the symbols you needed to decode were very faint and hard to read causing unecessary difficulty  but neither puzzle was impossible and as i enjoy decoding quite a lot i chose not to mark the game down for this  you may think otherwise  there is one sound puzzle that you must repeat over and over again for a particular reason  although this made sense within the context of the game i found it quite irritating and wished that i didnt have to do it after the second or third timeat the end of each chapter you must defeat an opponent in a game of strategya clue to the agon  i was initially a little intimidated by these games but managed to win each after  or  tries  you can also go back and play the games just by themselves after youve won theman entertaining bonusi liked this game quite a lot because of the subject matter and the hero  samuel hunt is an unusual man who is willing to sacrifice himself and take on dangerous tasks not to save the world but in the pursuit of his academic research  however his is the only character you will really come into contact with so if youre looking for a classicstyle adventure this is probably not the game for you  but if you like fist person puzzleheavy games and dont mind waiting for a definite conclusion give agon a try  i think you wont be disappointed
product: agon ancient games of nations the mysterious codex

review: first off it is important to know that i am a complete amateur when it comes to photo editing or drawing software i know just enough to get by in adobe photoshop and have bumbled around in other painting programs over the years so this is a review coming from someone who isnt skilled or fluent in these types of softwareso what did i thinkfirst of all anyone can easily turn a photo into a painting using the autopainting tool basically you just pick the style of painting you want from  choices including detailed painting impressionist painting and so on and hit the play button and your photo gets turned into a painting automatically i thought some of them like pencil drawing and pen and ink drawing were just awful when i tried it with a photo of my dog i barely got anything showing up you can then touchup the photo as you like using the brushes here is where i started to fall apart as i didnt find the program very intuitive i kept having to refer to the user guide to figure out how to do stuff and even then i wasnt quite doing it right so even though this is supposed to be a more basic program i didnt find it geared to amateurs like myself im attaching some examples to my review so you can see the results i was able to get basically doing nothing im including some examples of what i was able to do with the autopaint feature im sharing the original photo of my dog and then what i got when i used detailed painting impressionist painting watercolor sketch and pen and ink obviously there is a lot more you can do but youve got to learn how to use the program and make it work given time i could probably get more out of this program but given the review deadline i had i didnt get a chance to work with the software as much as i would have likedaside from making your photos into art there are a variety of drawing tools that you can use to paint on photos or just create a painting not being an artist i couldnt really think of anything to create from scratch but i think if you know what youre doing you might find these tools useful i used the desktop computer version and found it difficult to draw with a mouse i think if you used a mobile version for an ipad which i think i saw was available and used a stylus you would have much better results and if you had some artistic skills to begin with i tried to use some of the neat filters that were advertised on the box for example the kaleidescope effect but couldnt get them to load or work at all i followed the instructions in the user guide but felt like i ended up in an endless loop that never workedoverall for an amateur i think most youre not going to be able to do much other than turn your photos into something that looks more arty or painterly whether the price is worth it to do this or you can find other apps or programs out there to do this cheaper and better im not sure this was a bit of a lark for me since it was a vine product i thought i might be able to do more with this than i could but really found the program unfriendly to someone who comes into this totally clueless so for what it is worth that is my review
product: corel painter essentials  digital art suite for pc and mac old version

review: as is a habit of mine i tend to troll movie sites in my free time checking up on news and seeing whats being filmed where whos in what and so on in march  had a spotlight on natasha richardson to commemorate her life and acting achievementsit has been one year since she passed looking at her filmography i noticed that wild child was last movie she made i began combing websites like walmart and target for the movie but it is not sold in stores i wasnt going to buy a movie solely because it was natasha richardsons final appearance without first making sure it was halfway decent thank the lord for movie websites that is how i was finally able to sit down and watch this movie i have watched interviews with the cast and behind the scenes videos all over youtube and one thing is for sure i love this movie call me crazy but me a college student is completely enamored with itlooking at the film in scope is it original no it is not it is kind of a twist on mean girls meets a british academy for young ladies there is nothing especially remarkable about this filmnot in the slightest which is why i only give it three stars but that rating merely reflects the film as a public whole personally for me this film is way better than mean girls was mean girls was raunchy and i was about ready to strangle rachel mcadams for just about everything you see i believe that movies only work if the characters are dynamicstatic characters are a waste of everyones time and money whether literature or silver screen the characters in this movie are not staticeven the snotty head girl has to deal with changeit is recommended that this movie would only be good for preteens up through thirteen years of agepersonally i wouldnt let a child watch this until they were thirteen years of age the crudeness of british vocabulary and poppys mouth was at first startling i know emma roberts as the beloved detective nancy drew not as a teenager i would personally tie to chair for her attitude as such though is emma roberts character and having seen her do nothing like this and be completely out of her element in the british countryside was an eyeopener for sure emma roberts can be the brat as she can be the darling and she does by the end of this film make that predicted transformation she does of course push the limits along the wayallinall the heartwarming nature of the story contained within this roll of film is one i find worth paying for every cent emma roberts is a delight and british cast most of whom i had never seen before outside of natasha richardson as the meadmistress and the matron most notably moaning myrtle in the harry potter series and who were a delight to watch interact the male lead was handed off to one alex pettyfer upcoming beastly and while his role was small he held his own within the film amongst all the other ladies i applaud him for his bravery natasha richardson though with even a smaller role than alex who plays her son was a delight to watch light up the screen it was almost like seeing her in a new movie and that she really still was out there making movies and being a doting wife and mother her final role is a character that is a tribute to her as a person and as gentle a leader as her role as liz from the parent trap all those years ago while i do wish she had played a larger part her character was integral for the story to move forward and it made it worth whileif you are looking for a movie that is sassy full of quirky quotes that i personally love allusions to alice in wonderland and laughter as notorious as my own wild child is a movie i recommend with no hesitations as long as you understand that you are getting a comedy that is entirely british in nature but with a heart that can be distinguished from neither countrybuy wild child enjoy emma roberts as a brat and then a starlet and watch natasha richardsons final performance one that deserves more credit than it receivedand the movies keep coming
product: wild child

review: i may rate scrivener much higher as i get to know it better  it is rather soon to be asking me what i think of it  anyway i do a broad range of writing but what i enjoyed for the non fiction essay writing is the research section where you can put all the links to the articles and images you used for your work and refer to it as you build your essay  this is often a big issue for me keeping track of my sources  in terms of my fiction work another section i appreciated is the one for character sketches  i enjoyed putting together my descriptions in answers to the template questions  in addition i searched for pictures of the characters online and added those to the character sketches and that really helped me in terms of visualizing my characters  i just completely outlined my most recent book and i found that the outline feature combined with the cork boards helped me to structure my story really effectively  i enjoy the flexibility and the way i can adjust the outline as my ideas change  i like being able to bounce from research to outline to manuscript to notes to character and scene sketches as i progress through my story it makes my writing more  dimensional and more easy to travel through and alter and adjust  when i worked in microsoft word i found it very difficult to rise above a very sequential experience of the work i was doing  i believe that i have only touched upon some of the features of scrivener at this point because i just started using it  for example i know that as i am writing if i have a concern i can write a little side note which i can come back to laterthats great because your writing flow doesnt get interrupted  still have to see how that works  but there is a lot more  then once you are done you can save it into any kind of document you need in order to send it to be made into a kindle document or in a format your publisher would prefer

review: reader rabbit preschool has  games and one additional game that you earn  although there is a game that focuses on letters and sounds and one on numbers and counting the other three are all color and shape with patterns in the bugs game  the games allow your child to practice skills they have but doesnt do as much to help them learn as it could  if they dont know the skill they might get frustrated with a game  it does increase difficulty with success more colors patterns and tracks progress  from a programming stand point the game functioned well on my pc with windows mein bug matching baby bugs are dragged up to their matching parent  the bugs are irregular shapes with colors andor  patterns  the baby bug wont release unless you have it with the right parent but it doesnt appear that the number or choices is reducedin rainbow falls the child is ask to fill a particular shape and later a particular sized shape with the color  if the child picks the wrong color or shape they are told what color or shape they picked but the program never resorts to actually showing the child what shape or color they need to pickthe third colorshape game has the child picking matching gems in the mining game  if they pick the wrong one they get a horn but no further helpin the number game they are shown a rocket with the number and number of dots equal to the number of sparklenauts needed in the space ship  the child is told he has too many or too few but isnt actually told to add or remove x number of sparklenauts  every successful launch fixes a cloud but there are way too many clouds so this game tends to dragin rushing river an object floats down in a raft and waits for the child to choose the matching letter from the  choices above and shake glitter over the item  the beginning letter and object is named if you click on the object  the letter choices above are not named  if you choose the wrong letter it will tell you that but it never reduces your choices or gives hintsthe bonus game is has the child string movements together to create a dancethere isnt enough variety or difficulty for my son that just turned   my son that just turned  is challenged by the letter and numbers section but not the  colorshape sections  i would recommend jumpstart advance preschool for more variety and challenge
product: reader rabbit preschool  old version

leveleven with eight sets of twins and leaving most traits the same you have to change a couple traits even so this makes the games that care about zoombini traits ridiculously easy i often make an all random batch at zoombini isle partially to save time and partially for more challenge in the zoombini traits gamesone side of cliffs or caverns accepts one variety of the characteristic in question and the other side takes all other version of that characteristics this makes those puzzles simpler although maybe the higher levels have a  split also the caverns have you figure this out review: i have had almost no problems with this software and have to admit being perplexed about the wide range of reviews here many people are reporting all sorts of instability crash after crash problems with installations etc theyre obviously not making up stories but i havent had any of those problems except one i had no problems with installation it was smooth as silk and instantly recognized the capture card that came with studio  i installed studio in two other computers at the same time and had no problems with those either by the way i highly recommend getting the pci version it has ports for every type of video and is a snap to install  open the case drop the card into a pci slot and close the case the program itself has all sorts of new capabilities i did my sons wedding video with the help of a new feature ab editing and some of the new transitions i havent used yet the blue screen capacity or ability to edit in high definition but look forward to doing so the basics of the interface remain the same which means its as intuitive as ever it does its one job dvd authoring brilliantly studio comes with an actual manual and the book by jan ozer is an excellent complement to it i dont know about pinnacle tech support because while i have used studio for over nearly three years started with  ive never had to call it ive encountered a stability problem but even this is mitigated by the fact that when i restart studio it asks if i want to go back to the current project i click yes and am back exactly where i was before with nothing lost is this a big problem no is it an annoyance yes it may not even be that any more since i installed the free version  update i havent had a crash  and theres so much else good about studio that i cant take it out of  territory this is still the best video editing program in its price class

review: thanks symantecyouve officially change my attitude for the better about running security softwarei have to admit that when it comes to running security software i have never practiced what i preach  for example i installed antivirus software on my parents computer years ago but i almost never run it on mine  why  because ive grown tired of software that slows down my system but my parents care less about performance so its not a big deal for themwithout exception over the past several years every time ive attempted to put security software on my own computer antivirus firewall the impact on system resources has been frustrating  i think its dangerous to be without such software but every time i try my system comes to a screeching haltso after roughly another year of living on the edge i found a good price on norton internet security  and decided to give it another shot  i was absolutely amazed at how unobtrusive their software has become  nis  has actually changed my attitude about symantec a major culprit in the past in my battle to protect my computers cpu and ramheres what i noticed installation went very quickly  i didnt time it but im pretty sure the process took less than a minute updates went very quickly  it turns out that event though i bought this  version i was eligible to update to the  version for free  this process was simple and quick though i know it is running in the background and as an addin for my google chrome browser nis  and  has been barely noticeable  i am able to go about my businessasusual with no apparent issues from nortonabout the only time i observe norton doing its work is when i download a file over the internet  norton politely pops up checks the file to see if its safe and then disappears moments later when it is done checkingso as long as nis continues to quietly protect my computer in the background i plan to stick with it

review: i bought this and installed it on my asus eee pc  as a dualboot along with windows xp it is faster than windows  on slower computers but i have not yet tried it on the faster computers with the new windows  apps you can start doing stuff like checking your email as soon as the start screen loads instead of having to wait for all your autoloading windows desktop software to finish loading furthermore windows  starts hibernates and resumes from hibernation faster than previous versions it is not however compatible with everything that works in earlier versions of windowsin windows  you can set up a local user account or you can associate your user account with your microsoft account and this can be changed after you set up one or the other using your microsft account you can synchronize settings and log into microsoft web sites with one click in internet explorer you can also log into your user account with a pin instead of a password if you choose but it is optional and some people might consider it a security risk since it is just a  number whereas a password can have letters numbers and suchbefore you buy windows  you should consider compatibility if you want to install it on a computer you already have i would first run the windows  upgrade assistant available from the microsoft web site its free and easy to use and you dont even have to install it before running it it tells you whether your hardware and software are compatible on an individualized basisi would recommend windows  but due to compatibility concerns i would not advise anyone to replace their current version of windows with it you should either install it on a brand new computer possibly one you built yourself or install it as a dualboot along with your other operating system you can use the dualboot option if you have another hard drive or partition dualboot configurations work better if you disable fast startup from the power properties but if windows  is going to be your only operating system by all means use fast startupin short windows  is a great step in the progress of windows but make sure your computer can use it before you buy it
product: windows  system builder oem dvd   old packaging

review: i have been subscribed to spyware doctor  for over a year based on reviews in computer magazinesmost of the first years subscription was wasted with the softwares being deleted from my system because it was incompatible with my computer  it sent up blocking algorithms that wouldnt allow internet explorer to load  slowed my computer often to a crawl would crash my computer when coming out of hibernation and took forever to load itself to do a scan i have a  ghz  gb ram workstation with what would seem to be more than adequate resources to run even this bloated program  it did seem to catch some spyware that norton internet security spyware blaster and adaware in the aggregate missed in its long comprehensive scan but it just wasnt worth the incredible nuisance  i had many email exchanges with their tech support which was very prompt and polite and furnished several suggestions none of which seemed to helpwith the raves in the media and before all the negative customer reviews started appearing i thought my problems were due to conflicts which sd was confronting with other software on my computer as a specific problemwhen their latest iteration of version  came out i thought i would give it one more try and i guess being a glutton for punishment i recently renewed my subscription based on the encouragement provided by their tech support and the recent pc world review  well unfortunately it was business as usual in all respects other than the problem with ie  and startup time which had been solvedafter a few more exchanges with tech support they kindly offered to refund my subscription renewal cost and that was accomplished immediately upon my requestnow realizing out in the real world as evidenced by the numerous similar customer difficulties reported that this program however well intentioned is just not ready for prime time i would advise people to pass on spyware doctor  hopefully pc tools has gotten the message and is diligently working on version  which will successfully address the numerous problems that plague this program in its current state of developmentbottom line  avoidnot recommended

review: i am a longtime kaspersky customer  although the software works well the company  or its vendor  is suspect as to billing and unrequested automatic reenrollment  unless a user goes online and opts out of automatic reenrollment kaspersky will renew the users contract annually even if it is not requested  this could be a good move in that it maintains protection for customers who do not check their emails carefully for an expiration notice  however i went online and checked the box that removed me from kasperskys automatic reenrollment  i do not want to give anyone automatic access to my credit card  kaspersky sent an email confirming i was now enrolled for manual updating  i did this because i plan to switch to bitdefender  the next day i see that i have been billed for another year even though i still have four days left on my old subscription  alright i could accept this as a lag in the billing process that had already been in the pipe line  however the final insult is that the billing for the update to a longtime user was    this is for a download update  the price from amazon today for kaspersky pure is   perhaps the  difference is the kaspersky penalty for loyal customers  my suggestion  this is generally one of the top two rated protection programs  however if you sign up wait until the kaspersky charge shows up on your account and then change your credit card number  in this day of security hacks it might be a good idea to change your card number anyway

review: ive been creating websites with dreamweaver for years now and all that experience has taught me one thing  im a hack web designer  recently i have been trying to learn industry css standards and had heard that dreamweaver has made great advances in css management in  and  im embarrassed to say what version i am usingwhen i got a chance to get a reviewer copy of this training set i jumped for two reasons first i was mulling over spending the money to upgrade to dw  and i second i have always that i was missing out on a lot of dws capabilities  its now obvious that i should upgrade for the css management upgrades aloneas for the value of the training  i couldnt be happier  this is not an advanced tips and tricks resource nor is it an exhaustive boot camp in web page authoring but it is a fairly thorough training taking you from site planning and design to creation and publishing  i watched the videos from beginning to end and they start pretty basic with an html refresher then move to the meatier dw specific training  i can see myself returning to several sections later to brush uppersonally the css media and forms training videos were enough to justify the price tag  the training lessons were short and easily digestible  i liked that it broke training into  minutes so i had some time to do a little more indepth googling on subjects like text wrapping on absolute positioned css objects which it wont or checking my version of dw  what this is   an adobe certification training aid  so it starts from a very low level introduction and  goes through the entire dw web creation process   a wonderfully designed interface   a great overview of using dwwhat it isnt   a substitute for spending the time working with dw but it will jump start a novice   an expert tips and tricks referenceall in all i highly recommend this to anyone trying to learn dw or even web design in general the css placement section has been the most enlightening coverage of the topic i have been able to find  the authors delivery on the videos is great and the interface is the best most intuitive i have seen the only bad thing i can say is that the closed captioning is defaulted on so at times it covered the bottom of the properties table at the bottom of the screen so sometimes i had to close it to see things the author was pointing out  but all in all this is an absolutely wonderful product
product: learn adobe dreamweaver  by video core training in web communication

review: the quick take  the sony movie studio  suite provides a bundle with a lot of features for a very reasonable price  if youre looking for software that can handle a wide range of tasks and are willing to put some time into learning how to use it its a very good choicefull review i find i form longterm relationships with software  personally i dont want to invest the time in learning my way around a particular piece of software only to bump into its limitations  to find out that it doesnt perform or is lacking important features  so i usually narrow my options to proven software with a balance of performance and usability but with a bias toward features and performance  if that fits your needs sony movie studio  is a good optionsimple vs advanced  movie studio does have the option to choose a simple or advanced interface so it may help the transition for those looking to start by using a limited range of features and have the ability to switch to the advanced interface later on  or not  the software is a good value even without using all the features i know ill never use all of themvery good sound editor soundforge offers a nice range of features if you need to do additional editing on the sound  you can read reviews for it at the amazon page fornbspa datahookproductlinklinked classalinknormal  sound forge audio studio   note that it is not a multitrack editorbesides the video and audio editor a lot of other features are included  but those are the two components i use and those alone make it worthwhile for metouch enabled  its also not a feature i use but if youre interested in touch enabled editing its a new feature in movie studio  so you may want to look into reviews of that featurecheck your hardware  sony provides hardware requirements that are somewhat useful with respect to graphics cards you need a reasonably good one  i wish theyd provide better  guidance on that and with respect to processor and ram as far as i can tell they provide the hardware requirements for editing lowres video  sure the software might run on that hardware but thats not what people are buying this software to do  i have anbspa datahookproductlinklinked classalinknormal  geforce gtx  a desktop with an   processor mid to upperlevel  and  of ram while you might not need that much ram id suggest installing at least  to  if you can

review: i purchased this after trying out the free webbased demo the product seemed to match the way in which i prefer to learn a language ie start making sentences right away while simultaneously learning new vocabulary the exercises themselves are terrific and the tutor is great however this product has many usability issues which for me rate this product a huge disappointment for starters there is no way to run this on just a portion of your computer screen you are either running fluenz full screen mode or you arent so good luck trying to multitask or monitor any other applicationsalso there is no way to install this on your pc  you must have the dvd loaded in your dvd drive to run the software not a deal killer but very inconvenientthirdly there is absolutely no way to bookmark your current location within the lessons as such each time you start the software you have to find the lesson number you were last in and they arent named they are simply numbered and then you need to page through the individual workout sections within the lesson to find the last page you left off on this is very cumbersome and certainly not what i expected given the  price tag of the softwarefinally the record function within the speaking lessons does not work at all on my vista computer the microphone installed on the machine it is a brand new hp works fine with every other application i have including some emedia music software for some reason fluenz cant seem to produce the sound from the microphone even though the software itself is obviously picking up the signal from the microphone as evidenced by the onscreen sound level indicator support from fluenz was completely useless on this  no explanation no suggestions once they learned that the microphone works just fine with everything else on my pc so im giving up and sending this back for a refund no point in keeping a language learning product when one of its primary features doesnt even work

review: this is one of the first cdroms that has stumped my rather precocious daughter  she gets frustrated with it and does not spend hours clicking away at it  paradoxically i see this as a very good thing  in most of her other learning software packages there is no penalty for guessing and so she became adept at discovering the pattern needed to move on  they are really nothing but glorified multiple choice exams  simple by clicking on everything  sure she can learn a lot from them but i always saw it as allowing her to cheat as wellin this program if she gets something wrong she loses one of her little guys which eventually disallows her to move forward  so it doesnt pay to guess  she has to think about what is right in a systematic manner to move ahead  she also cannot backtrack and do something over  instead she has to go back to the start of the game with a new set of problemsi am also impressed with the logic portion of this software  the player has to recognise which features from sets and subsets in various contexts  that means systematic and abstract thinking but made fun as a game journey of creatures the player creates at the beginning though my daughter is stumped by some of it now she will really have beaten a challenging puzzle when she gets it perhaps with lasting impact on her reasoning abilities  visually while this is not as snazzy as some other cdroms it is pleasing enoughall in all one of the best learning cdroms i have yet seen  it really challenges my child which is exactly what i was looking forhighly recommended

review: im happy to say that i am  for the most part  very pleased with this upgrade so far  i came from vista  and i have now officially entered the  era by installing windows    for quite a few months i read about peoples experiences with the betas and release candidates and was excited about the good news i kept hearing  i decided to just be patient and put in for my preorder like most people did which meant waiting for the october  release datelets go through this topic by topicinstallation it was easy almost too easy  for some reason i was half expecting to wait more than an hour to get this on my machine but instead i was up and running in roughly  minutes or so i performed a clean install not an upgrade  and on top of that all of my primary devices were recognized see the end of my review for complete system specs  the windows easy transfer utility was an enormous help in getting my user identity and files into my new configurationuser interface personally i thought vista was very handsome what with its transparency  effects color schemes and usability improvements to windows explorer and i believe windows  continues that trend by looking just as sexy  if not more  while at the same time adding its own valuable features and enhancements  it just seems like a great deal of effort was put forth into making everything slick polished and logically consistent and ive already fallen in love with many of the additional improvements such as the revamped and more versatile taskbar jump lists and customizable themes  i havent yet become accustomed to some features like aero shake but hey those things are there if i need them  but the clean keep it simple approach the attention to detail and even minimalism in certain areas is certainly appreciated  and sure some people might scoff at the shiny facade and dismiss certain parts of it as being bells and whistles but honestly isnt it actually useful to have the ability to see fullscreen previews of running applications or to be able to hide all of your open windows and take a quick glance at whats underneath  all of these niceties simply add up to a more functional and usable desktopperformance i think its actually better than vista  overall the system feels more responsive and well snappier especially with regards to video performance  gaming is as smooth as could be  no complaints as far as startup shutdown and resuming from sleep mode are concernedstability very good but ill give  an a here  i got just one blue screen of death so far and that was during the installation of a particular piece of software i forget what it was to be honest  maybe a browser plugin  other than that its been rocksolid with absolutely no crashes  ive even gone through some software development debugging sessions in which the program i was working on was repeatedly throwing up on me and windows  recovered gracefully every timesoftware compatibility pretty high marks but not perfect  i think some of it has to do with my transition to  anyways like the fact that im having trouble with a specific component in visual basic  i use it to support a piece of software i designed for work  no big deal though  im going to circumvent it by using my copy of windows xp in suns virtualbox to run it so problem solved  another issue i had was the fact that the installation of samsung media studio  for my  player causes windows media player to fail to launch when i try to open a media file but again thats not a showstopper because i can manipulate that device directly in the os anyways without that application  and dont laugh but it looks like i might have to give up publisher   heh heh  yeah ive been using that program for years now to do miscellaneous desktop publishing but guess what  its installer is   so again thats a  lack of support for  issue not really a problem with windows  per se  plus i guess i could still run it in my virtual xp machine if i wanted to  other than those snags i just mentioned the majority of my applications and games run just fine  and thank goodness cakewalk music creator still works with my midi and audio interface deviceswindows live essentials i guess it was a smart move on behalf of ms  a little less bloat for people who would rather choose alternatives to those programs but still available as a free download  personally i feel that microsoft has been blessed with a lot of talented people who are really experts at design  the basic necessities such as live mail and calendar and all of the other apps are wonderful in my opinionothing things i like the devices section in the control panel is now much better and ejecting usb devices is quicker and easier  user switching works flawlessly  im a big fan of the ribbon which is the new user interface mechanism and visual style that is incorporated into the builtin tools such as paint and wordpad  i find it to be very fresh and innovative  im looking forward to upgrading from office xp to office   even calculator is betterbugs or quirks the link for opening the backup applet is broken but not when it is launched via the new action center  also unlike in vista mozilla firefox seems to have developed this strange problem of occasionally reporting that it cant find the server when i try to connect to certain websites that are listed in the results of a google search  but when i click the browsers back button the site will then appear and usually sites load properly when they are opened via the bookmarks menu or through other search engines  internet explorer  doesnt exhibit this behavior at all and the problem has started to bother me so much that i finally decided to install google chrome as my default browser i tried resetting my router and it didnt seem to have any effectin summary i think microsoft did the right thing by listening to its users and trying to correct vistas shortcomings whether real or just perceived  i cant say this is a revolution its more like evolution boy how many times has that been said about a software product  but to me its a step in the right direction and if things stay the course windows could have a bright caviar   gb sata  samsung dvdrw sata  lg bluray drive sata  creative sound blaster audigy   motu fastlane usb midi interface  emu  usb audio interface  yamaha  speakers  hp photosmart  printer  hp scanjet  scanner  dlink  router  microsoft natural keyboard  optical mouse  logitech rumblepad   windows  home premium

review: i have been a ghost user for a long time  it has always worked well for me  i recently lost the ghost disk after a move so i needed to get another imaging software  i decided to give true image a try  i downloaded the trial versionmy first attempt was to simply backup a hard drive and then restore to a larger new drive  simple enough  with ghost all you did was back it up and then restore to the new drive  the new drive was then expanded to the new sizeno so with true image  when i did the same backup and restore procedure i got the same partition size on the new drive and the the rest of the drive was unavailable  unless i wanted to create another partition which i didntafter spending a lot of time with their documentation  which i thought was very confusing i found out that i needed to delete the existing partition on the new drive and then need to use another utility option within the program  i then came to an option within that utility that asked me if i wanted it done automatically or manually  at first i chose manual and that would not work  i then tried automatic and it did what i wanted  i guess they intended the image to be an exact clone but that doesnt make any sense when upgrading to another hard drive  the other utility worked but the documentation was terribleacronis really needs to update their manual and make their menu system more intuitive to use  i find ghost much better in this regardoverall the product worked for me but i keep wondering if i would better off with ghost again due to the poor documentation it took me more than twice as long to get the same thing done as in an earlier version of ghost

review: instant immersion is a good budgetfriendly way to learn a language as it engages visual as well as auditory learning and helps you integrate the two learning approaches so that not only will you be able to read your new language but youll also be able to speak it  if you try to learn a language from a book only youll be fine at reading the language but might not be so adept at speaking and thinking in that language and calling up words when you need them  conversely if you learn from a program that is just cds or  where you repeat words and phrases you might miss being able to visualize what the word looks like  both approaches to a new language are important and instant immersion fuses them wellwhile this program doesnt have all the bells and whistles of rosetta stone its still a fine program for learning a new language and is a more budgetfriendly option  also in this particular package you get three levels of your new language

review: having purchased the reader rabbit learn to read with phonics i wondered if there was a similar excellent product for early math learning  unfortunately reader rabbit math though it has some fun games is a relic of an earlier era of educational software and is difficult to install on a modern system such as windows xp  reader rabbit math is an adaptation of an earlier game called math rabbit and as a result has some compatibility issuesboth reader rabbit and math rabbit make an appearance in this title as operators of two halves of a math carnival  unlike the learn to read with phonics series there is no story arc for this math game so it lacks the imaginative adventure that may help motivate some youngsters to keep going  this title is more like a conventional computer game in which players play various mathbased games to accumulate points  the two halves of the game are patched together somewhat awkwardly and when a player  chooses to play the math rabbit half the screen area of the game actually shrinks by about  perhaps reflecting older code that was written for display adapters with much lower resoltion than is available today  also unlike learn to read with phonics the software makes players choose what level of difficulty they want to set for each of the games every time you play rather than keeping track of a players progress and adjusting the difficulty automatically while keeping these configuration settings away from access by the youngsterswhen using the software with windows xp the program needs to run in windows compatibility mode

review: weve been using turbotax for about  or  years previously we did our taxes ourselves on paper we are a oneincome family who own our home and have young adult children in college  the first year it found a tax credit for college tuition i didnt know i could claim which was a happy surprise turbotax walks us through the steps of inputting our  interest and dividend statements i dont like to use other programs to input our information but it also offers to look for them online and autofill the info the schedule a for our itemized deductions is also easy to do after the first time of figuring out how it all works we donate to a number of organizations and it allows us to enter a list and the amounts of the contribution or value of goods which it prints for our records at the end it walks us through the process of entering our kids tuition statements then recommends possible deductions or credits then allows us to decide which will benefit our family most this yearthe biggest annoyance this year was that i couldnt get the search bar to work at all every time i searched a form it would stall out and never return the result it has worked in past years one of our kids graduated from college this year and i ended up having to download a  from the irs website to change our withholding allowances because turbotax wouldnt load it for me or show it to me not helpfulour son is an actor who gets  statements as well as smaller paycheck amounts that he has to claim as his own small business turbotax allows him to enter his  paychecks and he can also claim his  income expenses and mileage used pursuing auditions and acting jobs as a small business on a schedule c this was very helpful although we spent half an hour online trying to figure out the difference between business and commuting on the mileage screen they need to be better defined in turbotax fyi if you have a similar situation business expenses like headshots resumes and training go at the end of schedule c in other expenses not on schedule a under job expenses this issue also took a lot of research to figure outturbotax is generally easy to use and if you hit a snag you can click into the online help which is sometimes instantly helpful and other times not helpful and you have to pursue answers elsewhere when im finished filing our tax returns i copy everything that we used doing our taxes and burn it onto a data cd and make a print copy then delete it all from the computer the paper and cd copies go into a manila envelope labeled for the year when i start the next years tax return i load last years files from the cd then start turbotax its convenient that turbotax can look on your computer for past tax returns and automatically sets up your return for minimal busyworkthis year my taxes only took me a few hours to do including printing checking and filing i like the program and will continue to use it rather than paying someone else to do them which is costly or wading through the paper and math myself which is cheaper but a lot more work
product: intuit turbotax premier  federal  state taxes  fed efile tax preparation software  pcmacdisc old version

review: for most common and basic uses i think the quicken willmaker software is a good solution for those that want to do it themselves for their wills and other estate needs but i would caution that if your needs are not basic andor if you arent following most common and typical practices you may find this software is too rigid and not able to satisfy your needs in which case youd be left turning towards paying a professional or going with online solutions  if you approach the use of this software with that caveat in mind then i think youd be fine though it should be noted that the quality of this software also depends entirely on the quality of the patches and updates that are distributed by the manufacturer  if they break something while trying to fix or provided enhancements elsewhere in the product then you may wish you hadnt updated at all and instead used earlier versions of the product that perhaps more directly fit your own needson the plus side the product isnt too expensive at least not typically and older versions are normally reduced in price as newer ones are released so you can find an earlier revision at a bargain price if you shop around a bitif you are reading this review and wish that id say more about how easy it is to use the product or about features that i liked and disliked i didnt want to use the space here for that because i dont see the use of this software as something that id be going about doing constantly  this is a once a year chore if that  facing ones own mortality or thinking about what is going to happen with an estate after you are gone isnt something most humans worry about rather we all tend to try to ignore the fact that were all going to be leaving this world eventually  if the software is usable then im happy and this software is normally just that  i may have to adopt my thinking a bit to the way this software has organized the process but it still winds up being easy enough to get through  if it was truly horrible then of course id note that and offer the big avoid warning but that isnt the case herefor doityourself will and estate handling willmaker plus  should be fine  again those that need more customization or have more complex cases to deal with are best advised to work with a professional  the money spent now will be a good investment in the protection of your assets for future generations or whomever you select as your beneficiaries
product: quicken willmaker plus  old version

review: being first on the market with a brilliant idea does not guarantee youll get rich  but it almost certainly guarantees your competitors will do whatever they can copy your ideatrend microsystems accomplished two such brilliant ideas in  withnbspa datahookproductlinklinked classalinknormal  maximum security premium    usersa  one the first security suite that protects all of your multiple devices  desktop laptop tablet smart phone  and coordinates security between them  two first security program to install and operate mostly on a cloud cloudbased functions and features serve two purposes your devices interact and share data anytime on an alwayson cloud and with much of the programs footprint based on the cloud youve freed memory and resources for the devices themselvesput it all together and youre making real news a firstofitskind security suite that coordinates protection between your desktop laptop and smart phone simultaneously while freeing resources to make them run more efficientlythats the good newsthe bad news kinda bad for trend microsystems at least is that  months after introducing their brilliant idea the biggest names in security software each offer suites with these same or similar advancements  mcafee all access was rolled out in summer  and symantec introduced  norton   multidevice october from me though i salute the innovator   stars more if i could to the trailblazer

review: so much better than the windows voice recognition software  like a breath of fresh air when i switchedbegan using  first windows and then dragon after breaking my arm  dragon allowed me to effectively go back to work  i find it works well for composing letters and emails and any kind of writing where you are creating sentences and context  the software loves context and figures out the words very well  its much less helpful filling out forms or listening to single wordsi was able to get the hang of the navigation throughout my computer pretty well  i also liked the commands structure much better than the windows software  its smarter and i had far fewer errors  the windows didnt learrn as quickly and frequently couldnt respond to commandsthe software does learn and get smarter as you use it  can be a bit frustrating getting used to it but keep at it  it will learn your voice pretty quickly and become more effective for you as you keep using itit does require some processing power to run  if you have an old computer it will be quite slow and take up a lot of system resources  when i put it on newer machines it was able to keep up with my speech pace well and did not impact performance of my other programs  i tried it on  computers lenovo laptop  ran really really slow  almost unusable lenovo flex  laptop with  gb ram  runs very well keeps up with my pace of speech and very accurate  i do turn it off when i am not using it as it does take up some system resources to run in background zt with amd  ghz processor and  gb ram  runs best on this machine  very fast and no need to turn it off as it does not slow down my machinemake sure you disable the windows sr if you install dragon as you wont want them both running simultaneouslyi used an old cheap microphone and it worked fine  no need to purchase an expensive onei would definitely recommend this software for anyone who cant type well or is experiencing pain typing  i probably wont use it much now that i have recovered and can type faster than i can dragon but its nice to have the option when my hand gets sore  well worth the money as it got me back to work   weeks earlier than i would have otherwise

review: ive been preparing my taxes using turbotax premier online for many years now but this year i switched to using the mac desktop version of turbotax premier for the first time so i could import hundreds of investment related transactions from quicken  rather than try and enter them all manuallythe download from amazon over a dsl line took only a few minutes and the software installed perfectly on my  macbook pro running os x   there were  software updates that downloaded as part of the installation  one was very large and took some additional timeto convert from the online to desktop tax preparation and get my prior year tax data carried forward i followed the instructions i found on the turbotax web site  they had me start an online tax return for  which imported the prior years data then had me save download that directly to my mac  i opened this file in the desktop version of turbotax premier and continued preparing my  return as usual  everything worked flawlessly  i was able to export all my investment related transactions out of quicken  and successfully import them into turbotax premierthe software is easy to use and is exactly like the online versiona pro ive discovered with the desktop version is it seems so much faster to use than the online version  with the online version there are occasional lags presumably due to network congestion or overloaded turbotax servers  i may just continue to use the downloadable desktop version in the future because i like it so muchtwo thumbs up from me for turbotax premier for the mac

review: this program is pretty inexpensive and no its not going to teach you to speak french fluently  im not good with languages but ive found that making a run at french has required years lots of reading different books spending time with movies streaming audio over the internet and all sorts of things  this oneprogram isnt going to turn you into a fluent french speaker no single book piece of software or class willi didnt get much use out of most of the functionality in this product  but i do like the speech recognition very much  the program has a meter that gives you an idea of how well youre pronouncing words  its hard to get it pegged into the green at least for me but when i do i believe that im pronouncing the words pretty well  in fact i took a level  class at alliance francaise here in chicago and was as good as anyone at pronunciation and was complimented by my teacher despite being behind the rest on most other aspects of the language  this was entirely due to working with the speech recognition feature in an earlier version of this producti think its particularly helpful in light of the fact that language labs seem to be out of favor  at least they didnt use them at the alliance francaise  there arent many sources of help available for learning correct pronunciationif youre expecting this package to teach you french all by itself youre going to be disappointed  but if youre serious about learning how to pronounce things this is a great tool and for the money i think its a fantastic dealif anyone from the learning company reads this id like to suggest that they bring out a new product focusing completely on pronunciation and vocabularly  if they had a product with maybe  words and solid tools for learning the subset of the vocabulary you needed id pay a couple of hundred bucks for it at least
product: learn to speak french

review: the short versiondata rescue pc  worked perfectly for me and was able to recover pretty much every file that i wanted to recover from a windows  ntfs partition installed as bootcamp on the same drive as mac os x mavericks the longer versionthe scenario is that i had a drive with two partitions one being a mac partition and the other an ntfs partition long story short the drive was accidentally reformatted wiping out both old partitions then a single mac partition was created on the drive and a fresh copy of mac os x mavericks  installed onto it dohafter discovering this error i immediately stopped using this drive and configured it to be readonly to prevent further risk of overwriting files in the ntfs partition that if somewhat intact and not too badly overwritten by the os x reinstall was still lurking on the drivethis drive was then installed into an external enclosure and connected to a working pc running windows  i first downloaded and ran the demo version of data rescue pc  which showed me  much to my joy joy joy of joys  what looked like a mostly intact windows  installation complete with correct filenames i then purchased the full version the demo version lets you see what data rescue pc  thinks it can recover but it wont let you actually recover any files and was able to recover all of the files that i wanted nicei am so happy that data rescue pc  saved my a and got my files back i recommend this glorious piece of software engineering unequivocally also id like to mention the fantastic support provided to me by jason from prosofts customer support jason stuck with me over the course of several emails giving me the confidence that purchasing the full version of data rescue pc  would very likely get my files back in data recovery nothing is guaranteed but by being diligent and taking your time to thoroughly study your particular data loss situation you can make an educated decision and hopefully recover your files if your research indicates that it appears possible
product: data rescue pc hard drive recovery software for windows

review: i am an amateur photographer but have been involved in this hobby for many years  i also do my own editing and am fairly decent with good results  i have gone through numerous elements software and finally realized that i really needed to shoot raw  i chose to buy the lightroom software rather than sign up for the monthly fee with adobe  some of the items as a result are not available but for the most part i am very happy with the results  i am sold on lightroom  as a suggestion  if you have done elements and you graduated to lightroom there may be reasons for not wanting to into photoshop  just a recommendation  i have learned how to use lightroom in conjunction with elements   elements  will do a lot that lightroom cant do so i finish my product in lightroom and then  interchange to elements  to complete things like graphics panorama shoots hdr etc  once complete i switch back to lightroom and finetune my photograph which then gets sent out for printing  please consider using lightroom and elements  in conjunction with each other they are interchangeable  it is very powerful and gives you unlimited options with ease and great results  i am a strong fan of adobe and really like their products  small recommendation  if you want to really learn how to use both softwares simultaneously consider an  on line course  i learned the process through lyndacom  teacher kabili  their courses give you the broad view and dynamics of adobe products being used  you will become well rounded and really be able to move easily within both softwares  im very excited about both softwares and using raw has really given me unlimited options for photo editing  yes  this software  lightroom is a well developed piece of software and if used properly will give you the results your expecting  happy editing
