review: my personal favorite versions of microsoft office are   and  in my opinion  stinks but thats another story office  was in my opinion the first modern version of office and i still cry a tear for my friend clippy office  was the first version of office i would call truly solid with an amazing help system that i used as a helpdesk tech to solve many a problem freebusy errors anyone and office  after the cruel joke that was office  its a breath of fresh air to say the leastperhaps the biggest change in office  is the new tabs to put is bluntly tabs replace just about everything in the new office and pretty much any feature you want to use is part of a tabbed menu toolbar or window depending on your definitions another way to think of all these tabs is as massive sticky menus that can be slim as a toolbar or take up the entire screen it became very obvious to me very quickly that these tabs were heavily thoughtthrough by microsoft during development i like them a loti also like the overall smoothness of how office operates now the enormous reduction in crashes and bugs i have seen over office  and the overall feel and user experience i had actually been using abiword to type up amazon reviews and stories due to the way it draws letters and words but after using office  i can actually say that not only is it a pleasure to use but it is so workable and easy on the eyes that i want to use it for general writing something i thought i would never say in fact i liked it so much that i actually paid to get a home copythere are only two things i do not like in the new office compared to my other two favorite versions of office the help is terrible the incredibly helpful office assistants were great for learning faster and easier ways to do things but i have yet to find anything similar built into the new office likewise the search function of office  that returned incredibly relevant results now returns totally useless results most of the time for instance mail merge should definitely turn up instructions no matter how obvious the process is if you go through all the different tabs in the main screen toolbarthe other thing i do not like ismicrosoft support i purchased a copy of office  with a free upgrade to office  when i tried to do the upgrade the website refused to allow me to download it stating i had an invalid product id i ended up talking with at least  different microsoft support numbers as well as their online help and contacting amazoncom to boot and the process took weeks of calls in the end one of their semienglishcapable staff of which there appears to be about  people out of thousands finally figured out the source of the problem if you install a previous version of office and install a new version afterwards the product key displayed will be the old one instead of the new one and you will have to call microsoft and have them tell you what your product id is in order to upgrade i shudder to think what i would have done if the key had been bad with every single microsoft representative i spoke to refusing to send me either a copy of office  or a new key i can only conclude that the company does not value their home users in the slightest and would gladly take your money and then refuse to give the product advertised theres a word for this its called stealing i have been told in the past by admin in companies that i work for that the sole reason they continue to use microsoft products is for support if they treat their corporate customers half as bad as their home users thats a flimsy reason to support microsoftin the end i love this product though i have no doubt it will take me years to relearn how everything work that said i intend it to be the last copy of office i ever buy and since i have three copies of office  and two copies of  and each has three licenses it would be kind of insane to upgrade again unless it was free i highly recommend this product if you arent doing anything fancy or if you like me are a technical professional looking to keep up just forget about getting any good support either from inside the program or outside of it

review: this is an upgrade editionwe should cover a few things about the editions before we review vista starter is very basic and limited to  of memory almost everything good about vista is omitted home basic does not have the aero graphics flip windows special effects home premium has limited networking interaction vista business has the extended networking interaction vista enterprise has unix and virtual machine support ultimate has all the bells and whistles carefully choose what you want before you make this expensive purchaseinstalling vista is very easy checking with hardware vendors for patches and updates is a must windows vista upgrade advisor will identify the changes needed many notebook manufacturers will recommend an updates preinstall patch before a vista upgrade a vista upgrade will identify software on the system that might not be compatible depending on compatibility issues with an upgrade a clean install is also optional and works on notebooks although driver installations must be done after the install sequence is a matter of a few clicks and vista is up and running this might not be so simple if vista is loaded on a virtualization platform like vmware which requires additional configurations of the bios and some other tweaks we have come a long way since the days of windows  insert disc  the first thing that strikes the user is the sheer speed at which vista launches this is most certainly microsofts fastest os to date as soon as vista loads up low and behold the gadgets display appears on the desktop with moving pictures cpu meter realtime news feeds realtime weather clock notes stock exchange calendar and contacts wow impressive stuff but lets stop the press for a moment and tell it like it is gadgets is just apple osxs widgets rippedoff some might say that widgets existed before as separate plugins from yahoo called konfabulator but we are talking about this being inherently part of the os not plugins it is an apple invention that is in demand much like the need for a desktop recycle bin  which apple didnt patent doh microsoft settles for just straight out burglary of apples innovation and hopes that the user just enjoys it truthbetold in modern times when everyone is downloading everyone elses stuff for free microsoft are even in on the game and making money of it however this is all about competition since the competition exists and we may have some things to say about ms and monopoly we should be thankful that other forces are driving ms to do what it may not have done without these pressures  who really cares if vista is ultimately an apple osx rip this is what microsoft has always been about at the same time apple has openly accepted a command line interface ms rightclick save as or open as and intel chips balance things out if you dont like microsoft then you know where to go third party software will probably sway you one way or another however seeing  boot on vmware on top of vista is something that makes you stop and think linux users simply front customization as the bonus to not going with windows and in many ways they have a big point to make vista has the same lockdown start menu system you just cant change it or put any folder anywhere you want in a way this creates a standard where does johnny keep his documents on this system oh yeah the documents folder while at the same time professional users just want to custom the start menu the way they like it but cant microsoft hasnt really got a whole pile of originality going on here although there are many gizmos included and bundled in the ultimate pack and for all intents and purposes vista is osxvista is great its fast fast fast on a  pentium  or  core duo  of ram will run it no problem the first thing to do is to open a pile of windows hold down the windows start key  tab press tab repeatedly and watch as the screen turns into a flip  windows the new aero system also you can get a thumbnail preview of each running window on the task bar by rolling the mouse over it that is very impressive no longer are we pinned down to one desktop just scrolling through multiple windows in  is a sight to behold and in the eyes of many will make the upgrade worth every penny vista also looks a whole world better than xp and is no longer plagued with a boring sterile look vista is art but then again the gadgets play an enormous role in this apart from that windows now has a beautiful fade in and fade out of the windows some of which are transparent so you can see windows underneath this is a whole new art dimension that windows has never presented before and in many ways thankfully somebody decided to higher a graphic designer with all that money they make installing office  just brings it all review: years ago i used to edit video professionally using avid mediacomposer and after effects  i also had some experience with final cut pro near the end of that work  i then moved on to other things professionally and have not had the need to do any serious editing since then  i recently decided to cut my own home videos and needed to buy an editing solution  i looked for an avid solution since that is what i was experienced with but the company was essentially gone knocked off by apples final cut pro largely and while the software is still available it was very expensive and long in the tooth  final cut seemed the obvious solution but it is going a new direction as well and professional editors are vocally disappointed with it these days late  early   so i looked around at the consumer programs not expecting to find anything worthwhile  i was surprised by the available feature in videostudio pro ultimate and decided that for  i wouldnt lose too much my old avid rig cost near  just for the software  my expectations were still low but when the software arrived i was delighted to find out that it worked very well  i still havent had a crash   system  shocking  of course there are things that i could do on avid and final cut that cant be done on this software at least i havent found a way but that isnt surprising  it can do a lot and it works well even for longform videos  it doesnt bog down and it is pretty fast  the integration with dvdblue ray mastering is surprisingly niceas others have said the software is very intuitive  i was used to a keyboardbased editor which is fabulous when you are on deadline  a rapid way to work  but it has a really steep learning curve  the corel system is very visual and easy to understandevery time i use the system i am again surprised by the priceperformance  a great bargain

review: i had used print master deluxe  for many years but had to purchase a newer edition when i purchased a new desktop with windows   i looked at the ratings of the various editions of print master on amazoncom and found that print master  had the highest rating of any of the versions that could be loaded using windows   it also appeared that print master  should be able to open my old files where other newer versions would not do so  print master  with a rating of  stars appeared to be a better choice then print master  with a rating of only  stars which could not open my old filesprint master  loaded easily and it was able to open my old files  the only problem with some of the old files when opened was that not all of the graphics in my certificates could be downloaded including the border around the edge of the certificates  i believe that occurred because some of the graphics were not in the same location on my new desktop as on the old desktop and the border i was using was not available in the border library on print master   i did not like any of the possible borders in print master  so i went to the google images found a border i liked downloaded the border graphic to paint shop pro made the necessary refinements and saved the file  i had to do a few other operations before i actually had my certificates with the new border but they were very easy to do with print master i had several banners and almost all of the graphics downloaded ok for them  where the graphics did not download it was easy to replace them from their location on my new desktop with print master in general print master  is easy to use and operates much like my old version of print master deluxe   my main compliant is that the help information provided in print master  was useless in help me to creating a new border for my certificates  i probably played around for about an hour or more before i finally determined how to create certificates with a new border that i likedbeside the other positive comments i mentioned above you cannot beat the price of  that i paid on amazoncom for print master  and the software was delivered much sooner then estimated by the shipper  i gave print master  a  star rating mainly because the help information was virtually useless in helping me to deal with the missing border problem on my certificates
product: broderbund printmaster

acts like a mini windows explorer i clicked on the download file it read that bible just fine other than that microsoft does not offer me anything that i need i am happy with linux mint which is much like ubuntu i found all my favorite files it has a library of programs that i might like i installed my favorite games bible artha dictionary solitare  tetravex  specialty programs that i like i have a card reader connected to my ubuntu laptop the sd port will not read microsoft but the card reader does  so transferring my files is a matter of moving the usb cord to this computer  copying to the hard drive  the functions of the keyboard are similar to microsoft my screen is not tall enough so when browsing i push     then i mostly run the mouse to the top for navigation pushing  turns the function off too i use the artha dictionary to correct red underlined words the libre office spell check is easy but artha helps me find difficult misspelled words easier linux mint takes a while to load but everything works after installing  closing the cover for sleep mode is favorite it comes out of sleep mode quickly so loading is not a big problem  linux mint does have an interesting feature on office libre when you load office you have  a back screen that saves all your recent files so if you need a screen with multiple files you click on the dark x  it takes you to the screen with your recent multiple files click on the one you want start working instantly if you click on the top x it will shut libre office down  then you would have to reload it i like to keep spreadsheets of bills a organizer spreadsheet calendar word files  other concerns each month this way i correct the changes of each page  im done once you load artha dictionary it stays on the icon tray until you shut down but i usually prefer the sleep function by closing the lid  i guess for anyone that wants an easy to navigate program i believe that linux mint wins over ubuntu my big laptop has ubuntu  i am not about to change ubuntu after  weeks of  occasional updates  has no problems either  i laugh about my grandson his dad has a windows  computer when it hangs up he tells his dad your computer dont work so he is beginning to prefer the linux ones they dont hang up on him of course he is a genius  is spoiled so he losses his computer privileges often when someone complains that he is spoiled i tell them oh no all little boys smell that way  on mint  you can go to menu to find files if you use them regularly you click right click  add them to the panel this way it is always there for you on my panel are files like my computer firefox browser artha dictionary speed crunch calculator cheese for taking pictures rednote an organizer libre office writer  libre office calc  i do not recommend ubuntu  it is much like a windows  it wants you to sign up for a lot of cloud services i see no need for that i want all my files on my computer  some microsoft users frown upon libre office it is a very capable office program but some people do not like capable programs with simplicity  ease of use but i prefer office libre it has all the functions i do not need to learn a new version every year i can keep my files for as long as this computer functions but just in case save your important files to an sd memory chip that way if anything goes wrong you still have a copy  you do not need a key for any linux programs this xp computer now runs faster with linux mint  gives less trouble you do not need to do virus scans we do have updates they only take a few minutes at your convenience you can install linux on as many computers as you wish without permission  bit for xp computers  bit for windows  computers

review: i have a general working knowledge of several languages  studied in high school and college and through living and working in various countries  but have never formally studied french and knew very little of it ive been looking for years for a suitable program for it but have always shied away from the total immersion approach of rosetta stone from my albeit limited exposure to rosetta it seems that their lessons leave too many unsolved questions about whats going on to follow them youd really need to equip yourself with a grammar book and dictionary and be prepared to dig for lots of explanations the lessons dont supplythe theory behind an immersion program seems to be that little children learn languages much better than adults so we should try to mimic that experience with adults the trouble is that adults dont learn as little children do  and as the fluenz creators recognize thats both a plus and a minus its a disadvantage in that adults will most likely never master a language quite as deeply as a child an englishspeaking adult who learns french for examplewill never be able to speak french without at least a trace of an english accent but having learned english thoroughly before learning french is also a huge advantage english speaking adults can leverage their existing knowledge of how a language english works to learn the target language as adult english speakers we already understand the many forms we need a verb to take for i you she we they so when we learn the i form we look for the he form and etc because of the knowledge we have of what we dont know we make much more rapid progress in the target language than a child couldbut we can do so only if we are given explanations that correspond to the questions we naturally have for a simple example we naturally wonder why do you say you are going en france but a paris its unnecessarily frustrating if the language program you use never bothers to provide you with the simple explanation that you always use a when you are going to a city but not necessarily to a countryeach fluenz lesson begins with a short intro then goes to a dialogue which provides information and vocabulary relevant to tourists each lesson develops and expands upon the grammar introduced in the previous lessons because most people traveling to francophone countries will be interested in getting the basics down lessons often center on being in a cafe and ordering food or with traveling from place to place or asking questions at a hotel these short dialogues can be listened to with no subtitles with subtitles only in french and with subtitles in english and french after the student has listened to the dialogue the instructor comes on and goes through what the student has just heard line by line adding additional relevant information as well as mnemonic devices to help students retain the information the instructor also adds related concepts or structures to those introduced in the dialogue subsequent workouts encourage students to practice through reading writing listening and speaking what i find particularly delightful are the little comments the instructor sprinkles in along the way about some element from film or sports or culture once the instructor mentioned that the bidet was one of frances great gifts to womankind i doubt ill ever forget that line as it was so unexpected and human a remarkas much as i love this program i would have given it  stars rather than  if that were possible because the software is just a bit glitchy you have to play around with it in order to get it to work properly for example you might in a given workout get just one question and find when you hit next that the workout seems to be done there is no way to move forward within it what you need to do in that case is select next workout and then go back  and backwards  until you complete the previous workout it took a while for me to realize this so i missed some valuable practice along the wayoverall fluenz is an excellent program long overdue i look forward to learning my next language with fluenz
product: fluenz french  for mac pc iphone ipad amp android phones version

drive and thus is usable on netbooks and other portable devices  it now remembers where you left off so you can pick up there again without any wasted effort  the program can be minimized though still only displayed on the default monitor as far as i can tell  the license is the most flexible of any program you will buy and i can use it on my laptop and netbook  all in all a worthy upgrade that review: heres my true assessment as of being a hallmark greeting card software user for over  yearsoverall the goodi use this mostly for my business where i have to keep in touch with clients so i send cards to both clients and family  having used hallmark software for over  years i can attest to the quality of this software  overall i am happy with the software and the cards this can produce  overall the cards are nice there is a large variety and you can customize most of the cards by using the art studio feature which allows you to alter the text and greeting or insert your own graphics and photos  in some cases the text is built in and you cannot change it because its part of the design but for most cards you can change the text  this means you can find a funny one meant for an uncle and you can switch it up to read brother instead of uncle  if you are creative enough you can even create your own cards from scratch or just edit the cover and text of an existing card for a completely custom look  another great feature is that when you install the software on your machine youll end up with all the hallmark fonts used for the greeting card program also available for use in word and other programs on your pc  i have been able to run this and older versions of the hallmark software on my windows   bit machine without an issueprintingprinting is easy and best done on a quality color inkjet printer  the colors come out truer on inkjets rather than laser printers  ive found by using laser printers the colors are dull and often there is toner staining that make the card look less professional and more amateurish  drawings and graphics print best on plain or textured paper where photographs print best on high gloss photo paper  the drawback about using photo paper is that you cant print the inside the card using the backside of photo paper so ive solved this by printing the outside on photo paper and the inside on plain paper and mounting the plain paper as a liner inside the folder photo cover  it makes the entire card look much more upscaleprinting double sided is easy just follow the online instructions for setting up your printer and you are on your waypaper and envelopesfor best results use high quality heavy card stock when printing your cards  the heavier weight stock adds a high quality feel to the finished printed card  ive never bought the hallmark papers and envelopes that they sell to be used with this software as any cardstock and envelopes will work and are generally much cheaper  the only thing youll be missing is the hallmark crown embossing on the envelope flaps but ive not found anyone who even noticed this  i go to the office supply store and buy greeting card envelopes measuring   x    they come in pastels ivory bright colors etc  pick up a ream of textured card stock in at least  to  pound weight  the pound measurement indicates how thick the cardstock is  the thickest your printer will accept the better  choose a plain whiteivory in a nice texture such as linen laid felt textured shiny glossy speckled etc  for most card printing projects i use off white felt textured for printing cards with drawings cartoons or illustrations and glossy photo stock for printing cards that have photographs  again when using glossy photo stock use a plain paper liner to insert into the folder cover  send the print job to your printer and instead of flipping the printed page over just insert a blank piece of paper and it will print the inside greeting  fold both the cover and the insert and use a glue runner or glue stick to affix the liner to the card  glue the back of the liner near the foldoverall the badthis software is not all that perfect  i dont often upgrade until several years have passed between versions  i find it irritating that when you own the  version and you upgrade to the  version half the cards appearing in your older version are still present in your newer version  when you pay to upgrade you should have all new cards not reruns of the old stuff you already own  they tout the fact that you will get  cards which is not a lie you do but they dont tell you that about  of those cards are from the previous version of their older software  after several years though most of the older cards are cycled out and they do put new cards in their place  so if you want to upgrade wait for several years before you dohallmark used to sell packets of new cards so you could keep upgrading and adding to your collection  they stopped doing that around  or so  it was a great feature because you could just buy new birthday cards if you wanted while keeping all your older cardsafter a while the cards in your existing collection will become stale  once you send a friend a card you cant really reuse it for that same person  you have to mentally keep track of which card you sent to whom  it would be a great feature if you could tag each card and add a name of the person you sent it to in order to keep track better  hallmark are you listeningsome of the greetings are kind of lame  there are some witty ones and some well written ones but there are many that are corny or seemingly outdated  how  does this greeting sound  like dawning after darkness like sunshine after rain things will seem much brighter when you are well again  it sometimes feels as if hallmark doesnt always put their best work in this collection so they can still drive sales of their cards in the store  fortunately there are enough to choose from so you can usually find a greeting card that fits or you can insert your own text to customize itsummaryoverall i would rate this product high and give it my recommendation  if you send a lot of cards you will save money by printing them yourself even if you buy high quality textured paper  the cost of a greeting card often exceeds  or more for the nicer cards and if you want to send personalized cards this is one of the best software packages available
product: hallmark card studio  deluxe

thousands of pictures the workflow is easy to understand fast and has good sorting and selection capabilities the innovative stack tool is especially useful for sorting through dozens of nearly similar options of the same shot on my macbook pro unibody  intel core duo i am not experiencing any performance issuesmany reviewers focus on aperture as an excellent raw workflow tool and while it certainly is that it is every bit as useful for your jpegs in fact i primarily shoot jpeg except for when i expect to run into unusual exposure and color issues for which i will also shoot raw for my needs i find that shooting raw is quite often overkill and as a bonus transferring and processing jpeg is much less time consuming and requires substantially less storage spacethe adjustment tools may remind you of iphotos except there are more of them and they are much more capable and sophisticated that being said aperture is not a fullfledged image editor and many users will want to use aperture in conjunction with an external editor such as photoshop or photoshop elements external editors are well integrated into apertures workflow from within aperture you will be able to address most exposure contrast and color issues thanks to the strong tools in this category as well as retouching cropping rotation and some noise reduction issues all of these adjustments are performed nondestructively and can be undone selectivelyaperture accepts plugins and comes with one included in the box dodge and burn when using plugins aperture creates a new tiffversion of your original file actually more precisely of the version of your original file that you are working on my only objection to this workflow is that if you need to use several plugins on one image eg a dfine  noise reduction followed by some dodge and burn and perhaps pro contrast from nik softwares colorefx pro you end up with a new tiff file for every plugin you use as aperture plugins do not operate in layers like they would in photoshop for example i should also mention that i have on occasion experienced some stability issues with aperture and they almost always occur when using it in conjunction with plugins however these crashes have never compromised the integrity of the database aperture users will most often store their libraries as an aperture managed databasei have also produced a couple of photobooks which i have to say i have been very happy with the quality is good not as good as if you print your own on a highquality printer but good nevertheless youll find fewer predefined layouts than in iphoto but the ones that are here are more geared towards professionals one feature that seems to be lacking and that i have found useful in the past with other photobook vendors such as blurb is recommended resolutions for each photo based on the exact dimension of each frame with such a tool sharpness is optimized for each image that being said the lack of this tool did not seem to affect image quality too much in the aperture books that i orderedall in all aperture  is a very strong product and one that i now rely on entirely for my workflow i recommend getting a book about aperture i bought apple pro training series aperture  which will help you use the software more efficiently especially since the included documentation is pretty weak
product: apple aperture  old version

review: ive had fluenz french for a few weeks and can tell you that this product is great  i am particularly impressed with the software and its focus on teaching french to adults with clear explanations and examples  the lessons and workshops are filled with colorful photos which help you stay focused and attentive  each lesson builds upon the previous one so each new lesson acts as a refresher  i was surprised at how quickly i was able to learn french and remember it  also the lessons are short enough that you can do them in the office during a lunch break  the basic format is as follows  first you listen to a short french conversation three times  once with english and french subtitles once with french subtitles only and once without any subtitles  you can repeat the conversations as many times as you wantneed  i tend to listen to it more than three times   then the instructor breaks down the sentences and the vocabulary explaining usage and grammar   finally workshop follows where you read write and speak what youve learned and variations of it  overall a great product that i would highly recommend to first time students of french

review: expression web and the whole expression studio shows promise in one day being the best web design toolset available  but this  version is bound to frustrate two typesfront page fans and vista usersin regards to the front page fansthe days of being able to visually design a fully functional professional looking web page appear to be over  coffeecup and sitespinner come as close as anything but both are very limited  control of the technologies employed across the web htmlcss flash ajax php dotnet sql with plenty more to come appears beyond the reach of any one product or company  i dont particularly like it  monopolies have their upside  i would pay dearly for a decent visual web designdevelopment program that was truly wysiwyg but having searched for well over two years ive concluded none exist or are on the horizon web developers simply have to accept using multiple programs and text editing for certain tasksthat said as a hybrid visualtext web production tool along the lines of dreamweaver expression web offers a lot  i found its draganddrop functionality its preview capabilities its cssphp integration its handling of imported objects superior to that of dreamweaver  as the expression studio evolves i can easily see it rivalingsurpassing adobe design suite in terms of workflow and interoperabilityparticularly as it promises better compatibility with the rest of officebut the  thing is still basically in its beta phase  pay  to be beta tester  it is seriously buggy and it does not like vista with office installed  the help files dont work  it will constantly reinstall and reconfigure itself upon startup  it will crash a lot  i have seen zero improvement in these problems over the past  months and have tried numerous improvised fixes suggested on web forums without any luck  microsoft appears to be gearing everything toward a  release of the expression studio that integrates it with its new rival to flash silverlight rather than fixing the buggy as heck  version  this has been supremely annoying and likely has soured many of the studios potential adopters

review: update i originally gave this product  stars the  version of fluenz addresses the original concerns i and others raised about the inability to pick up where you had left off in a previous session so i now rate the  version of fluenz as  starsthe good the teaching method works it is essentially a classroom on my laptop with an instructor who explains the lesson ie conjugating the verb to want followed by speakinglisteningwriting drills the lessons build nicely the drills not only reinforce the current lesson but also contain review from previous lessons building ever more complex sentences fluenz has obviously put a lot of thought into organizing the progression of each lesson while the vocabulary is focused on the needs of someone on vacation it is far more than a phrasebook on dvd the program is also teaching prepositions noun genders and verbs but in a context that a tourist would find immediately useful where are you from my hotel is not far from here do you want to eat with us at the restaurant i already feel that i can create my own sentences from the building blocks ive been taught this is in sharp contrast to my high school german where we learned such immensely useful phrases as i have ten fingers while there is no robot accent checker you can record yourself and play it back to hear how you sound alternating with a native speaker this approach works fine for mecons the provided audio cds and downloadable podcasts are good but the printed materials are little more than a pocket survival guide in keeping with the classroom paradigm i think some printable notesflashcards for each lesson should be included at this pricebottom line i struggled with languages in high school and i am definitely learning with fluenz which is whats most important the cost of the program is comparable to two semesters of night classes at a community college so i dont think the price is out of line

review: i bought this because of the price and the reviews  i had taken part of a semester of japanese at the city college and boy was i disappointed  i have a good deal of language learning experience and i just felt like the teacher i had was making it way too complicated although i think she was trying to make it easier in her defense  it really isnt all that difficult of complex a language  its simply mysterious because of the writing system and grammar differencesheres my advice  take the hiragana and write down the first ten characters  repeat repeat repeat until you can do it from memory  then add ten more  repeat procedure  you will have all of your hiragana and katakana down in no time  honestly a couple of days would suffice if you really want to learn it quickly  once you have that down you will feel like you have your feet on the ground and the rest will not be so scary  if you would like to practice you can google hiragana practice or something like that and find quite a few little quizzes or games etc  thats a good way to keep it currentanyway human japanese is exactly that human  its not going to treat you like a robot student and try to program you with information  expect to be told digestable amounts of information  it will obviously be quite different than english so just accept it and move on  things will start to come together before long and you will find there are some things you actually understand  this is encouraging  now and then bits and pieces of cultural knowledge will come up to break up the lessons and keep it from getting boring  this is all done in a very friendly way as if you were learning from a gentle tutor who just wants you to enjoy learning and eventually understand  honestly this is how it should bealso customer support is very friendly
product: human japanese

review: i have installed and reinstalled this product many many times  i have a computer with three separate window users  i selected a user for the actual installation and the product installed without a hitch in the selected user  however for the other two users  the security center component of the product opens to a blank screen and  my internet explorer registry entries seem to become corrupted  i can restore the ie registry entries with a fix provided by mcafee  however after doing so the security center continues to open to a blank screen  however the program seems to be working properly in all other respects and the only problem is the blank screen issue when trying to open the security center  although this is a nuisance i do have full access to the security center screen for the user that was selected to install the program  i have used mcafees free chat support but they have been unable to help me and i refuse to pay for telephone support which is never free  i strongly suggest mcafee amend their policy to permit free telephone support for installationrelated issues  chat support tried to help but after several contacts it seemed that all they were doing was repeating themselves  if you are ok with the possibility that access to the security center may only be available in one user profile then you should be satisfied with the program overall  it could be a problem however if access to other users on your computer is passwordprotected  compared to norton internet security suite my computer does not seem to be bogged down like it was when i used norton prior to moving to mcafee  incidentally the problems with mcafee were encountered after being  certain norton was off my system completely  i also have xp home edition with service pack  so i wonder if the new service pack is causing the issue with the blank security center screen on two of the three users  mcafee does not seem to think so but sp  is very new and there have been upgrade issues going from  to  reported

review: i waited to complete the entire course before writing this review and in no particular order these are my observationsi should tell you that my web skills are limited i used front page for years and have created several very elementary dreamweaver sites for family members im in the process of trying to work more professionally cleaner less and better code and more creatively a less stilted and more unique and appealing design this course doesnt purport to be a web design course it assumes that you already have a basic idea for a relatively simple website and its going to teach you how to implement it dont expect inspirationpositive level absolute beginner to intermediate  it is entirely dvdbased the booklet  pages including index that comes with the dvd just provides additional random information it is in no way connected to the content or the sequence of the course the scope of the information presented is all that is needed for basic competence in the implementation of a simple dreamweaver  website you do become familiar with the dw interface the workflow best practices web and dw terminology and basic website structure and creation the sequence and progression is logical and sequential there is some reiteration of basic principles as the course progresses to clarify how something previously explained applies in a new situation the interface is very well thought out you can go backwards or forwards easily it has constant access to a table of contents that allows you to search by both topic and subtopics in case you want to navigate to a completely different topic it allows you to bookmark with long notestoself on topics of interest you may want to keep coming back to the interface coloring and design are neutral and unintrusive the screen always retains focus and the surrounding options melt away the course has the secondary purpose of preparing for the adobe certified expert ace test each main section has a practice test at the end another asset is that the video transcript is captioned under the viewing screen optional this is particularly helpful if youre in in a public place where you cant turn on the sound all explanations of hardtograsp concepts ex the box model are clearly demonstrated with visual examples as a matter of fact this is the clearest explanation i have ever seen of the box model i did find the booklet section on fireworks instructive since i have never used that program in the past in fact the entire booklet is very instructive and usefulits just totally unrelated to the course on dvdnot so positive coverage of other concepts such as content placement and positioning are a little more basic and less detailed than i would have liked i cant recall or locate now any reference to floats whereas ap divs and frames both older concepts are well covered the narrator has a pleasant voice and clear diction but is somewhat monotone and unexciting there is no search function or index this makes it impossible to look up a term or a topic that is not specifically listed in the table of contents i would have thought that the transcript text might have been searchable but it isnt for my learning style i would have preferred that the booklet function as support material for the video so i could follow along with text that directly reinforces the visual demonstration and is easier to go back to or use as reference material the bookmarks that you create when taking the course on your laptop are saved to that computer if you want to change to your desktop the bookmarks obviously are not there so as a personal index these bookmarks have their limitson the whole i do recommend this course i wish i had taken it earlier because it laid down the groundwork better than an online course that i had just taken however i think that for a person who is learningasyougo not just learning general theory but actually trying to apply it to a real website it is essential to have reference material on dreamweaver  some sort of guidance on design principles and a solid html and css anthologyall in wellindexed booksvideo and online courses teach you very well how to build their sample websites but when you are stumped on your website you need to be able to supplement the general principles they taught you with a more onpoint reference
product: learn adobe dreamweaver  by video core training in web communication

review: one year update jan  please see my original review below the updatei am still trying to finish a house we had some strange turns in our life so i am not a typical user when i bought the program i was trailing electronically behind an architect who was doing the work by hand eight months ago we moved and started all over with out house i am happy to say it is now almost finished when i got into that level of design i upgraded to chief architect which is the professional program i was able to rent it by the month to match our project there are a few steps to go through to be able to read a chief architect professional program on home designer but once you know it is no big deal i am still very happy with the program even with a high level of skill there are some quirks but that is not uncommon with a lot of computer programs after being a daily user of both of the chief architect programs here are a few pros and cons the pros far outweigh the cons and the improvements seem to be the ones that people were most interested in seeing changed kudos chief architectpro absolutely the best tech support i have ever experienced there are scads of video tutorials that are free the manual online is searchable even with poor organization of search terms when you dont quite know what you are trying to ask about when you do need a persons help someone is right on the phone with you to help i made a really big mess once and they asked me to send a copy of my entire file for them to review they posted an answer for me i was so surprised and they are just downright nice folks the  modeling allows you to do a lot of things i did not know as an early user for example you can pick a chair paint it with an eyedropper like you find in most color editing programs and then save the chair so you can use it again you can upload actual photographs and use them for your backgrounds so you can see how a project will look some of the irritating problems with grouping and aligning have now been fixed the align function works like powerpoints does the snap to functions are much much improved it is rare that i have trouble with this anymorecons it is still relatively expensive both the home designer pro and the professional chief architect programs are priced well for what they are but they are not priced for most casual users aligning floors and keeping paint colors in the rooms where they belong can get tricky you have to break the wall lines to keep the colors where they go which then sometimes causes the floortofloor alignment to get wonky setting ceiling heights in multilevel houses with twostory vaulted rooms is recalcitrant there are clear directions on how to do it but sometimes the program reads the space where the floor would go as missing and thinks that your ceiling heights are different which then locks your ability to change ceiling heights below this happens not too often but too often for me to not be frustrated i have learned to deal with it but it took me a long timeoriginal review jan  one reviewer raised the issue as to whether or not the reviewers actually used the program i am an actual user of this program i have other reviews posted at amazon and aim to provide information to others to help them evaluate whether or not a particular product meets their needs my review is long but i have endeavored to enumerate the key things that i have learned i like this product very much but do not think it is for everyone if it meets your needs i can recommend it highly i am extremely happy that i selected it when compared to other optionsmy summary reviewhome designer pro is an excellent program for amateurs doing real architectural work it is not a substitute for a program that a professional might use but it does have many of the same features it is very detailed and allows the user a deal of control however without experience or practice it is not an easy program to use if the extent of your computer software experience is ms word excel and powerpoint do not expect that you will be able to get right to the meat of this program those who bring to the desk knowledge of computers and of design and building will be the most quickly successful the price moves the program out of the casual users budget but it is well below a full professional program i believe it is an appropriate price for a program that yields such professional results for people working on their own or on projects of limited scope among similar programs i believe this one is the most robust for the knowledge and skill that the user has to bring to the tablebackground of my goals in purchasing the producti purchased this software hoping to have a program that would allow me to do real architectural activities not just draw floor plans my house burned down in one of the  summer wildfires in the rockies and the dwelling reconstruction is complex and i am very involved in the process i was reticent to spend  on a program that was marketed for nonprofessionals i decided to purchase the program after talking with their sales personnel who were very helpful and clear that if i did not like the program i could return it or upgrade to the professional version there are many things you can do in the fullblown professional program that you cannot do in the home version but overall i cannot find many things that an amateur would be missing if you are planning to be in business using the software i would recommend the professional line that is twice and more the cost of the home designer pro otherwise i think this is a fine productthe learning curve is steep i came to the software with experience in multiple statistical mapping and graphics programs the most basic functions were not hard the more complex and helpful functions are not click and go the require a thoughtful approach accompanied by experience in the software and patience with learning i estimate that it only took me a couple of days to learn to draw basic floor plans place furniture and fixtures and create a  model it took me more than a weeks worth of effort to learn about doing exteriors in relationship to the floor plan and the  renderings it took about another week to learn how to get the roof functions to work after about a month working with the program i can remember how to do stuff and can do most anything i want to do the work that i produce with the program is professional and is useful for the actual planning and building of my home it is something that can be used for bids and built from which makes me very happy i would like to be clear that it is not a substitute for a good architect or engineerthings that i like about the program it is very robust you can make mistakes and recover from them the file protection protocols are very good if you are working and forget to save the program automatically saves it for you it is not easy to overwrite versions of your document reducing the oh no function if you make changes and forget to save them or if you change and dont do a save as finding the previous file is a snap each time you open your file you will be prompted to select the one you are opening or a newer version it is nice to have the options the array of products and materials is truly astonishing one of the differences between home designer line and the chief architect line the professional line is the amount of access you have to materials there are more available in the chief architect line but the number and variety of products available in home designer is impressive it is possible to import information in multiple formats including jpg and tiff it will import dxf files but not dwg i have found this to be somewhat frustrating but interoperability between various cad programs is not as seamless as other types of programs the import and export protocols are generally excellent and allow you to import cad furniture etc from other places for example you can import backdrop jpgs so that you can have your  model sitting on the actual property where it will be built many product companies provide their catalogs to the users of the program for example sherwin williams paints are available you can also import gps coordinates the materials list function is extremely helpful you can compile the list by room by floor by building or by the entire project you can sort the materials so that you can view by all of your materials in a searchable categorized master list or by the total materials needed for a specified place within your larger project for example you can request  materials list for all bathrooms or one bathroom you do have to be very meticulous with the general building materials fittings fixtures and furniture that you use in the home because the materials list will catalog exactly what you put into the program early on i kept making duplicates of cabinets when i tried to place them i got  dishwashers piled on top of each other in such a way it appeared to only be one i got a bid back that included  dishwashers since that was on my list  the process seems to work best using it within the chief architectpro program but you can automatically export the files in comma delimited excel or html formats the computer requirements to run the program are not all that intense the computer requirement in how you use it are pretty important for example some products will not render on some computers with less power you can have the program installed on multiple computers if you move from one computer to the other to work you simply deactivate the license on one and reactivate it on the other the change is not hard and takes less than a minute to do i like being able to know clearly what i am doing with intellectual property it is nice not to have to guess if you are or are not following the specified rules the snaps and grids are robust you can draw a pretty poor line and it will straighten right up if you miss getting walls connected you can fix that by selecting one of the lines and right clicking select join line and then click on the other line the program is organized so building it is really nice to be able to show other people what you are thinking flat floor plans are extremely useful and are immediately clear to some people however i have found that i can do the  modeling and truly convey what i am thinking even if the other person has not been working on the project or have experience with reading blueprints the doll house views are extremely useful and downright fun the full model draws all of your floors say foundation  and  stories you can click up and down the stories and look inside of each floor you can look down useful to see if your framing review: i am a college student who uses a computer for all studying yes ive come up with a workflow for math too the copy restrictions on ebooks makes this workflow impossible so i make my own scans and use ocri used abbyy in the past but i wanted something that would better read math characters better format pages and better recognize images i bought omnipage ultimate because it was recommended to me by the salesrep who said omnipage would be able to do these things properly the rep because i bought naturallyspeaking student edition as well gave me a large discount on ultimateoverall i saw omnipage ultimate to perform satisfactory for ocr software but the issues with large files were a dealbreaker for mefirst the pros very good formatting of word documents very good ocr small footprint in memory    mb for me even with several large documents openomnipage ultimate had an edge over abbyy in preserving the formatting of textbook pages headers footers paragraphs and titles were all placed almost exactly as they were on the original page the images it recognized were wellplaced too however it did not recognize complex mathematical formulas as images  but as a discombobulation of garbage characters it would also confabulate graphs that contained recognizable characters a con best mentioned here is that omnipage would sometimes flip pages the wrong way and there would be no messages about the program detecting the possibility of a page having the wrong orientation a feature ive yet to see or find in abbyy or omnipage is detecting outoforder or missing pages via the page number in the headerfooter ie the scanner grabbed the wrong page first or two pages were glued togetherat the heart of the program  its ocr ability  i give it high marks uncertain characters were uncommon and i did not often stumble across incorrect characters omnipage occasionally preserved bold and nearly always recognized italics when i enabled the greek dictionary omnipage even recognized some mathematical characters i have not yet tried this in abbyyomnipage seems to be efficient at keeping a small footprint in memory and does not consume much of my cpus resources even considering only the cores it actually uses ive had several documents open at once each roughly averaging  and omnipage will only consume  of memory omnipage worked relatively fast with smaller documents approx less than  size and demonstrated a linear performance curve with ocring larger documents however i do recommend restarting the program after extended use because it may bog downnow the cons some are dealbreakers for me very slow at saving relatively large documents seemed to handle  pages well but performance for  pages exponentially decreased very slow at opening relatively large documents same here large documents may be corrupted ouch no happy medium with pdf output sizequality pdf document output is either extremely large and high quality or extremely compressed and relatively low quality some scanners are not fully supported check the list could use some improvement because abbyy does this well in my experience weird randomly deleted characters in titles of image scans workflow inconveniences frustration with not being able to find help or search results related to these problemsnotefor the troubles ive had i must first mention that i have an  amd  of ram windows   and an otherwise wellfunctioning computer when the program ran smoothly there was a respectable impression on  of the  cores when the program slowed to a crawl and struggled with large documents the cores were barely above idle and memory was about twice the norm    there seems to be some sort of bottleneck in the program where it becomes increasingly unable to utilize system resources for saving and loading larger and larger documents this seems to be exponential as an approx  page document with the same scanner settings as a  page document took several times longer to save and load  in short larger documents were saved  loaded more slowly than they should have otherwise been  pages took about  minutes  pages took about  minutes  both for saving and loading finally my  page document  selfscanned and errorchecked while putting up with this programs sluggishness  was corrupted with a file io error for every page after saving for a third time yes i spent around three hours just waiting on the program to save and load the file a few times omnipage finally ruined the opd omnipages proprietary native document format after i had it ocr the whole thing and save itfor a highquality pdf i must select optimize for quality in the searchable pdf save options window this generates a pdf that can be anywhere around  times the size of omnipages own opd for the documentfor a highlycompressed pdf just select anything but optimize for quality yes optimize for size   etc all do the same thing compressionwise  for the background image there is no compressionratio slider for mrc or most importantly the background image mrc options which are unavailable when optimize for quality is selected have a noticeable effect on appearance of text but account for little of the size of the file for background images there are only options for jpeg jbig flate lzw adobe xi turns up an error when lzw is used and losslessmediumbest compression changing any of these options for the background image produces roughly the same result in file size and image quality  which are always tiny and highly compressed abbyy seems to produce similar to smallersized pdfs that look betterthis is a big thorn in the side for me i have a fujitsu  its flatbed scanner is very fast in addition to its adf  its a highspeed scanner allround when i use omnipages native interface it only lets me use adf i have to go into the menus each time i want to change scanning preferences unless i use the twain driver when i use the twain driver interface i can use the adf or flatbed but i cant seem to find the option for continuous flatbed scanning i have to roll my office chair from the scanner to the computer select add more pages then select scan in the twain driver each time i want to use the flatbed with abbyy its native interface allows me to choose between the adf and flatbed and the pause interval between flatbed scans  each time i scani am not sure how to accurately describe what is going on here when the scanner scans a page and it gets imported into omnipage sometimes chapter titles large font seems to be the key will have missing or filledin os ds and cs they will be completely erased from the source image  replaced with the adjacent background color unavailable for ocr and missing in pdfs or they will be filled in with black coloring  unavailable for ocr and appearing as so in pdfsthere are some little things about omnipage that prevent it from truly shining i cant cover everything in detail but these details are nonetheless important first if i insert pages into the adf incorrectly they may be out of order or rotated wrong the only way i have found to fix this in omnipage is delete the pages and try being more attentive the next time i insert the pages i cannot run a command to reverse the selected pages order or correct frontsidebackside order and i cannot select multiple pages and flip them all at the same time i can change processing options in the optionsprocessing window to insert newly scanned pages beforeafter current pages which is convenient  but i cannot renumber pages without selecting and dragging which can be very slow and cumbersome image enhancements seem to be limited to either being done one page at a time or via image preprocessing in the optionsprocessing windowfinally with all of the tech issues ive had in omnipage i have not been able to find any documentation forum posts or help topics of others having these issues

review: i am not an security expert and i dont pretend to be one in real life this review is based on what i found and my own preference on how security software should function you might look at it differently but hey this is my review go write your own i completely trashed norton antivirus  in one of my reviews on pc world and i read a lot of users had similar problems and turn away from the product back then so i am going to do some comparison  to its old self and give it some justicebefore reviewing for this particular software i want to get to  points because they are going to be relevant latter in the writing security software is like a car insurance you really dont know how good it is until something bad happens and you are caught in the middle of the mess no virus zoo tests perform by independent labs can emulate what is going to happen in the real world i am just need to get it out there the first line of defense is the user not the antivirus software if the users are clicking on random links and running  softwares while downloading torrent something is going to go through no matter what you have running on the computer unless you are running linux then your risk is lower it is almost impossible to remove a virus once it excuses on your system someone out there is going to tell you it is possible but my response is always the same how do you know it is all clear look up rootkit on wikipedianow back to the review this writing is based on few standards i have  does it actually slow down your system  is the user interface clean enough antivirus  won me back i have been a norton antivirus fans up until  that was the time symantec lost it that was a period of time where norton antivirus itself functions more like a virus it takes forever to startup program would lag for  to  seconds after i clicked on it wrost scanning a  gb drive took  to  hours to finish a lot of users were complaining about it an i was one of them who switched to a different software nod  if you care and it is still a great software symantec took the feedbacks and completely rewritten their engine at first i was skeptic and continued to use solution that was little known to people back then  and kaspersky mainly because they were light and have great detection rate kaspersky was the first antivirus offered hourly update while other offered update every  to  days after my  license expired recently i decided to give norton another look and man i was impressed the software load up pretty fast on my computer intel   gb ram windows  with little system slow down just like  norton finished loading into memory in few second after login and just sits there waiting for the next action  solution such as kaspersky sorry kaspersky you used to be one of my two favors will take a minute or so to finish doing something i dont know what that is but the something is writing to and from the disk constantly for the first minute or so when kaspersky was on the system even with boot timescan options turn off this happened pretty often for few other software brands i am not going to point them out one by one user interface is something most of the antivirus software designers dont get they are either super complicated that makes you feel like you are about to launch a space shuttle or they are so simple that nothing can be change at all i remember the norton antvirus from old day had about ten taps on the type of scan you can turn on and off from the program such as pop smtp integration to word and outlook aim ie etc i remember writing a review on pc world a lot of these options are pointless forced integration into other software will only a slow the third party software down and b likely to break when the third party software update for example the integration into aim never worked for me because i was using a green version of aim that didnt have ads another thing that stuck to me was the notification box back then the software would pop you a notification and let you know it is working on something that is the wording norton antivirus is working on background tasks something along that line  but it doesnt tell you what the tasks were and no potion to pause it what is the pointnorton  is a lot better the user interface is easier to navigate i like the new design where it lightup at areas where a virus is reported it is pretty options are fairly easy to access and the scan option is right there at the first page so i dont have to look for it furthermore the software tells you when it was last updated and whether there is a problem and the notification is no longer intrusive thats is great although some of the options are still confuse ie the reputation scan why cant this be part of the smart scan doesnt bad reputation often means ad ware and reliable scan this sounded like something from the norton system work days but this is an antivirus why do i want to know whether a file is going to crash save it for norton so does it detect  virus in real world i dont know it is more of a blind faith look at it this way if the software tells you it caught something it must be working but when you dont get a wanring in  or so days while you are doing daily tasks does it mean it is working or does it mean something got through the realtime protection and you just dont know about itthe good thing is norton antivirus  appeared to be doing pretty well on all the independent lab tests along in reviewers from pc world and pc magbut then again the user is the first line of defense you got a flu shot doesnt mean you want to let other people sneeze at you

review: i have used turbotax for several years and have had generally adequate success with it some iterations have been more trying than others but overall i found the deluxe  product to be somewhat better than in years past the return appears to be accurately prepared and the interview interface is less confounding in some areas than in the past the capital gains and charitable contributions sections though are sometimes needlessly convoluted and the worksheets produced if you want to print the whole thing for your records are mammoth my return with all records and worksheets was  pages long each charitable contribution got a three page charitable organization worksheet that is nothing but a waste of paper if you give to a lot of charities each year which i do the dimensions of your records will astound you of course the actual return for filing is much smaller so saving the full set on a cd is most likely adequatethe other irritants are the aggressive promotion of turbotax premier if you have any interest or investment income i have used premier in the past but dont see any way it would have helped me in my situation it may help some people with more complex returns but if you have runofthemill interest dividend and capital gains income deluxe is probably sufficient i do think the badgering from intuit to buy ancillary services is a bit better than in years past honestly besides the pitch for premier and audit defense its pretty benign for  the interview is extensive and worded in a much more userfriendly way than in years past there are still occasionally puzzling questions to make you wonder what they are trying to get at but their help section was able to make quick work of it i had a question on a property sale and it was quickly resolved one thing i would like is for intuit to make it easier to enter data in the order in which you wish as everyone has different recordkeeping and organizational systems you can skip around but its much easier and less errorprone to do it in the order which they have devised another issue which i find extremely irritating is getting to intuits privacy policy and opting out of mailings email etc from them it is a real challenge to find this and i recommend doing it right off the bat if you want to because otherwise you will forget about it i did it when i registered but even then i believe i had to search for privacy options with the help functionfrom an ease of use vantage point installation download of my state return data and updates were a breeze im using a windows machine and i had zero problems with the program itself which is a huge blessing i have not been as lucky with some previous incarnations the questions took me through every aspect of my finances for  and with the exception of the property sale question i couldnt find anything it overlooked i have used turbotax in most of the last fifteen years and found  to be one of the best years yet i have tried the competing hr block software taxcut in a few years and while it produced adequate results i found the interface to be much less userfriendly than intuits though i didnt use it this year of course and as a result i plan to use turbotax deluxe for  as well

review: the life application bible from tyndale house publishers is one of the best bibles i have read it has a timeline showing the chronology of bible events along with important world events this allows you to understand how the biblical events fits in the world history  each book of the bible has a book introduction with vital statistics that describes the purpose of the book author historical setting key verses key people and a blueprint which gives a summary of the book  there is a map in the beginning of each book showing the key places of events in the book  also you will find character studies of different biblical characters like moses davidetc  all over the bible there are foot notes throwing more light into the verses at the end of the bible  there is an index to the notes and there are few colour maps a carefully organized crossreference runs along the margins of the bible text  i find this bible easy to read without straining the eyes with large clear print  also the foot notes are not disturbing when you want to skip them and focus on the biblical text this bible is little heavier than the slimline version but the clear easy to read text and the notes definitely outweighs the weight

review: i hope this review serves to clarify some of the complaints that people have posted regarding office prefaceafter being disappointed with leopard  which i also reviewed i kept using tiger when finally  arrived i began using it it fixes many leopard bugs according to some websites at least  bugs have been fixed this is important since many problems with third party software may be related to other software or to the operating system for example apple is aware of problems with its sync services and core image also some bugs have existed for many years and have not been fixed such as a potential bug when moving data to an external devicekeeping these issues in mind i did a completely clean install of leopard  in a brand new hard drivei installed office  as well as the available upgrade to first impressionssome useful features have been added such as elements gallery which may be a time saver for many people some features have been removed such as vba and this may be a dealbreaker for many peopleim keeping office  in a separate partition in order to use previous versions of word and excelat the same time i can still use the new versions when i dont need the vba featureslack of vba support was announced well over a year ago so this came as no surprisestarting upeach program took approximately  seconds to launch office seems to have a peculiar way of handling fonts though and launch times can be greatly effected after installing another program that installed more fonts and installing extensis fusion to manage my fonts launch times for office programs was approximately  one hundred and fifty seconds instead of the original  ten secondsnow it takes about a minute to launch these programs in all fairness the slow down is partly caused by third party softwareoverall and very brief  impressionspowerpoint works with presentations that used to crash my  version the  version was practically unusable for me this was a welcome upgradeexcel works fine and the elements gallery is a good addition it lost vba support and the abalysys toolpack i kept the  version as wellword seems to be a solid upgrade some third party templates do not work with  so i kept word entourage works very well i had to reselect the folders that i had set up for my rules and reapply categories to my folders syncing with address book always adds many duplicate contacts fortunately there are scripts to deal with this inconvenience hyperlinks still require a workaround as mentioned by another reviewer i would not rate office with  solely based on that issueexpression media used to be called iview mediapro iview multimedia and iview many years ago it used to be a  shareware program when i first used it eventually it became quite expensive so i never upgraded until i received this version so far im happy with it it has worked fine for cataloging thousands of fonts and pictures and im entitled to a free upgrade when version  comes outpricethere are free office alternatives as well as iwork i still prefer microsoft office for the most part the only exception may be keynote microsoft offered a substantial discount under the names of the technology guarantee program and the super suite deal additionally for one day they offered a  rebate so users could get the mac special media edition for approximately  with these offershad it not been for the offer i would have stayed with office  ive used office  for a few days every day and so far have encountered no problemsoverall im satisfied with the upgrade support has been great both by microsoft and the mvp people search their forums and youll find a lot of useful advise
product: microsoft office  for mac special media edition old version

review: i returned from a trip to greece about one week ago and i found garmins greece mapping software to be not only worthless but rather a penalty  my wife and i were initially confident we had the garmin with us but it quickly became apparent in the peloponnese and later in crete that the appliance nuvi  and software could not be relied on  the garmin led us around in circles along the small circuitous roads of rural greece  sometimes it would get us to our destination but only after asking the locals did we realize that we had wasted a lot of gas and time in locating our target  do yourself a big favor and buy a good greece roadmap and ask the locals if you are headed in the right direction  after the aggravation we just put the garmin in the glove compartment followed the street signs and asked people if we were going in the right directiongarmin refused to offer a refund in spite of my lengthy explanations stating that they have a nonrefund policy for maps  fair enough if it was the users fault but i used a garmin street pilot iii in the us for ten years and loved using it  this nuvi  in conjunction with the greece mapping was a total disaster even for an experienced gps user like myselfone concrete example of the ineffectiveness of the greece software and garmins lame explanation is when we routed our garmin for athens upon leaving sparta in the peloponnese  i chose the city option to guide us from one of greeces larger cities to its largest  you cant get much more vanilla than that  i lost count of the number of times the appliance directed us to exit from the national highway which connects the two cities  so the nuvi didnt even recognize one of the few major highways in the peloponnese  when i asked garmin about this they told me it was necessary to input my preference for highways in the gps  apparently garmin is admitting that the default setting wants to lead you along old back roads to your destinationthe fact is however the nuvi never recognized the national highway connecting the two cities  i asked garmin when the latest update occurred and they said it was fairly recently  asking greeks in athens however i found out the national highway was completed sometime before  for the athens olympic games  who is fooling who  where is your  integrity garmin  you are like a bakery trying to sell week old bread as fresh
product: garmin city navigator for detailed maps of italy and greece microsdsd card
